title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar, then add other ingredients.
Bake at 250° for about an hour.

title: great-great-grandma paul's chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa with a small amount of milk. Scald remaining milk.
Stir in sugar mixture and stir over medium heat until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve warm with cream.
Serves 4 unless one is my brother, David.

title: cashew pasta chicken salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain and rinse with cold water.
Place in 7 quart container.
Add remaining ingredients except cashews. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add cashews and toss gently. Makes 25 (1 cup) servings.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let set for 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil; boil for 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the jello. Pour into jars and refrigerate.

title: no-friller-cornbread
directions: Prepare mix as directed.
Mix in corn.
Bake as directed.

title: oriental asparagus salad
directions: Cook asparagus in boiling water to cover for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender; drain.
In bowl, while warm, combine with well drained bean sprouts.
Add dressing and toss lightly.
Chill well.
Spoon into lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving:
162 calories, 6 g protein, 10 g carbohydrate, 13 g fat and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except parsley, together.
Place in individual shells or Corning dishes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix thoroughly until smooth.

Add a few drops, if necessary. Squeeze through pastry tube or cut in narrow uniform lengths using a knife or pastry wheel or roll in a long roll and refrigerate, then cut in thin rounds and place pecan on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken in enough water to have 2 cups of broth left after cooking.
Remove meat and line bottom of a deep dish with cut up chicken.
Pour 1/2 cup milk over chicken.
Pour and spread 1 can cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Mix dressing with 2 cups broth until soft.
Spread dressing over chicken, covering all of chicken mixture well.
Place in a 400° oven for 55 minutes to 1 hour.
When dressing is brown, it is done.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon and onions in a large skillet until meat is browned and onions are tender. Drain meat only if there is an excessive amount of fat. Stir in ketchup, salt, mustard and vinegar. Combine remaining ingredients in a 3 qt. casserole, stir in meat mixture and cover. Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly. Garnish with strips of bacon, if desired.

title: chrusciki (holiday cookies)
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and brandy; continue to beat.
Add sour cream and flour alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Transfer to well floured board; knead until dough blisters.
Cut dough in half; roll very thin and cut into strips about 4 inches long.
Slit each piece in center; pull one end through the slit.
Fry in hot fat until lightly browned. Drain on absorbent paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: quick and easy cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add the eggs one at a time with 1/2 cup of sugar.
Continue beating until smooth.
Place filling in prepared pie crust.
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes until firm.

title: special eggplant subs
directions: Beat eggs. Place bread crumbs in separate bowl. Dip eggplant in egg, then in crumbs. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crispy cool. On bun, place lettuce, eggplant, red peppers, cheese and tomatoes. Sprinkle with dressing. Enjoy!

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Split and remove the seed from jalapenos.
When splitting them, don't cut in two.
Leave them intact.
Stuff with shredded cheese (only use 1/2 pound when stuffing), then close jalapenos back together.
In a separate bowl, mix together the 1 pound of uncooked sausage, 1 cup Bisquick and the other 1/2 pound of shredded cheese.
Take this mixture and roll or pat it around the stuffed peppers to make an egg shape, then put them on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: apple crunch crisp
directions: Cut up the apples and spread them in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. Melt the butter and stir in brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and sprinkle over the apples, pressing in lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: redfish supreme
directions: Marinate fish in pan with juice of lemon, Accent, seasoned salt and white pepper for about 2 hours in refrigerator.
Melt butter in skillet. Shake flour over fish and cook in skillet until lightly browned.
Add vermouth and simmer until flaky.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Have ready one baked pie shell.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly in a lightly greased 3-quart casserole. Spoon vegetables over rice.
Pour chicken broth and water over the vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir well.
Cover and bake another 30 minutes.
Garnish with mushrooms and parsley, if desired.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Drain juice from clams and keep in saucepan.
Add cream cheese and flour.
Heat until thickened.
Add cheese and clams.
Season with Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Serve with Bugles.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then combine water and vegetable oil. Add liquid to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add flour until dough is no longer sticky, kneading as you add flour.
When dough is no longer sticky, allow dough to rise 30 minutes.

title: vrazene
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix yeast with remaining ingredients except flour.
Add flour.
Knead for 7 to 8 minutes. Let rise for 2 hours.
Roll like hot dog buns and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Split with fork and toast under broiler until golden.
Great with butter or cream cheese and served with coffee.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1 cup of sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and 1/2 cup of butter.
Pour into baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/3 cup butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter crispy treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large (3 quart) microwavable bowl, combine everything but the cereal until blended.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until surface is bubbly.
Add cereal, toss until well mixed.
Press into pan.
Cool.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, then flour, milk and flavorings.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut cookies.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, parsley, milk, cheese, butter & garlic powder until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8-10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes 8-10 biscuits.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Put flour and cornmeal in bowl. Add a couple of dashes of salt.
Add water, stirring until the consistency of thick pancake batter. Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot oil. Turn once, browning on both sides.
Drain on paper towels. Eat hot.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a casserole.
Top with 2 cups Stove Top stuffing mix combined with 1/2 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients but cornflakes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; mix well.
Put crushed cornflakes on top evenly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean salad
directions: This is one of my favorite recipes.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Mix onions, bell pepper, celery, cheese, corn, green beans, celery soup and sour cream. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Top with margarine or butter and bread crumbs. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chewy raisin walnut shortbread bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. Combine flour and sugar. Cut in margarine until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into pan and bake 20 minutes.

title: spicy pastry
directions: Add pumpkin pie spice to dry ingredients.
Combine molasses with water and mix in just enough to moisten dry ingredients.

title: toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts. Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until light brown. Makes about 5 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pistachio pudding mix.
Add pecans and marshmallows.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie crust.
Cool; set aside.
Cook the first 3 ingredients until clear and thick.
Add jello and food coloring; cool.
Place freshly prepared and sliced strawberries into crust. Add cooled mixture.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Prick the potatoes several times with fork. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add 6 cups milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons onions, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Stir in sour cream. Add extra milk for desired thickness.
Serve with remaining cheese, bacon and onions as garnish.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, mix sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Blend flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chopped Butterfingers.
Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon (depending on size cookie you want) onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand on cookie sheet 2 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Put roast in 1 cup water in roasting pan.
Add bay leaves and oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook at 350° until tender.
During last hour, add carrots and potatoes that have been sliced.

title: south-of-the-border-dip
directions: Combine refried beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spoon mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread sour cream over bean mixture and top with cheese.

title: one pan pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Stir all ingredients except chips and nuts in pan with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute. Stir in nuts and chips.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean (45 to 55 minutes). Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen from pan and cool.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and spices alternately with coffee.
Fold in apples and pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until center springs back.
Makes a moist cake.
Can serve alone or with Cool Whip.

title: cucumber and yogurt salad with fresh herbs
directions: Peel the cucumbers. Cut each in half lengthwise. Scoop out the seeds and thinly slice the cucumbers. Sprinkle with salt and put into a large colander to drain for 30 minutes. Meanwhile in a large bowl, combine the yogurt, vinegar and herbs and season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix next 5 ingredients and add to macaroni.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs and garnish with tomato wedges.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.
Serve on lettuce as a salad or top with melted orange marmalade for a dessert.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: white buttercream icing(for decorating)
directions: Put ingredients in mixing bowl; beat for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit and cream pie
directions: Prick pastry shells with fork.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of shells and bake at 425° until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread half of this mixture over the bottom of each cooled pie shell.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs, beating until creamy.
Blend in salt, corn syrup and butter.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pastry shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix salt, pepper, chicken broth and soup together and bring to a boil.
Combine rest of the ingredients and make a batter.
Pour broth mixture over chicken and spoon batter over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 425° oven.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Over low heat, melt butter and chocolate.
Turn off heat and add Milnot and eggs; stir well.
Add salt, sugar, vanilla and cornstarch until smooth, then add coconut and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.
This will make 2 regular pies or 1 deep dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in greased casserole. Sprinkle top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: southwest chicken rice casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine brown and white rice, chicken, onion and tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a shallow, 2 1/2-quart casserole, place half the mixture.
Cover with half the sour cream, chile strips, cheese and all the olives.
Add a second layer with the remaining rice mixture, sour cream, chiles and cheese.
May be covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours.

title: fabulous fried onion rings
directions: Combine flour and beer in a large bowl and blend thoroughly, using whisk.
Cover bowl and allow batter to sit at room temperature for at least 3 hours.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Combine cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and margarine.
Sprinkle 1/3 in buttered casserole.
Cover with a layer of oysters and repeat.
Add Worcestershire sauce to milk and pour over contents.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: beef and rice
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix in onion soup mix, cooked rice and water.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: instant cocoa mix(a great christmas idea)
directions: Keeping all ingredients in their original dry form, mix thoroughly until well blended.

title: banana nut bread
directions: On wax paper thoroughly stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
In a medium mixing bowl beat eggs slightly; beat in banana puree and butter.
Add flour mixture; stir just enough to combine.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn into a buttered loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° until cake tester comes out clean, about 55 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack; turn right side up, wrap tightly with Saran wrap..
Store overnight before slicing.
Serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water, then add cold water, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Freeze overnight in small containers, i.e., quart Tupperware bowls, 24 ounce cottage cheese containers, 8 ounce Cool Whip containers, takes several.
Prepare punch approximately 45 minutes before time to serve.
Place frozen punch in punch bowl and pour 2 bottles of the ginger ale over frozen punch.
You may save one small container of frozen punch to freshen up the punch when you pour the last bottle of ginger ale into the punch bowl.
Will serve approximately 45 to 50 people.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except the last four.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut up cabbage and add with sugar and vinegar.
Remove meat.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Discard bones.
Season to taste.
Garnish with dill.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Dissolve cubes in hot water.
In saucepan, melt margarine; blend in flour.
Add broth slowly, stirring.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients and heat until mixture bubbles.
Serve over biscuits, rice or toast.

title: ice pops
directions: Pour the orange juice or Kool-Aid into the ice tray.
Next, put the plastic over the ice tray and put toothpicks in.
Put in freezer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Take out of freezer and you have Ice Pops.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Combine and mix well.
Bake in 2 layers at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes, until done.
Let cool; cut layers in half to make 4 layers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Keep in refrigerator overnight, then serve on crackers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Put butter and brown sugar in 8 or 9-inch skillet. Cook until waxy. Put pineapple slices in bottom of skillet to cover bottom. Mix other ingredients together. Pour over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Let set in skillet 2 or 3 minutes. Turn out on plate.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together well the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla extract.
Set aside.
Slice the cookie dough rolls into 1/3-inch slices.
Place slices of one roll into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; press dough together to cover the bottom of the baking dish.
Spoon the cream cheese mixture evenly over the dough.
Top with slices of the remaining package of cookie dough.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and the center is slightly firm.
Remove from the oven, cool and refrigerate. Slice and serve.

title: german skillet supper
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; spread cabbage over butter. Arrange potatoes in a layer over onions.
Sprinkle potatoes with caraway seed.
Break beef over potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 to 35 minutes, until potatoes are tender and meat is cooked through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles(easy)
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: stuff
directions: Prepare instant pudding mix and blend in Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, layer pudding mixture and graham crackers. Top with cherry pie filling and cool 2 hours.
Serve chilled.

title: lee's lemon pecan bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat butter on medium speed of an electric mixer about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk; beat well after each.
Stir in pecans and lemon peel; pour batter into a greased, floured 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan; spread evenly.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Serves 16.

title: company pickles
directions: Cover whole cucumbers with boiling water.
Allow to stand overnight and repeat this procedure on the next three mornings. On the fifty day, drain and slice in 1/2-inch slices. Combine sugar, spices, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days.
On the third day, bring to a boil and seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: no-crust cheesecake
directions: Beat together cream cheese, 2/3 cup sugar, eggs and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until smooth. Pour mixture into buttered 9-inch pie plate. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25-35 minutes (till puffy and brown around the edges). Cool cheesecake 20 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Grease and
flour an 8 or 9-inch square pan; set aside. Separate eggs.
Add
soda to egg yolks and mix.
Add remaining ingredients,
except
for
egg
whites
to	yolk mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat
egg whites until fairly stiff and fold into cornmeal mixture.
Pour
into prepared pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between paper towels to remove moisture. Press hash browns onto bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate to form a crust.
Drizzle melted butter over potatoes.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven. Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt butter in frying pan or wok.
Add beaten eggs and stir to keep cooked egg pieces small.
Stir rice and meat, mixing thoroughly.
Add soy sauce and stir until color of rice is fairly uniform.
Add vegetables and continue to cook until heated.
Meat and vegetables are optional.
You may add several kinds or leave out all together.
Serves 4.

title: bread pudding with meringue
directions: Scald milk and a little orange rind.
Beat 1 whole egg and 1 egg yolk with salt, 6 tablespoons sugar and nutmeg.
Pour hot milk into egg mixture.
Add bread.
Turn into 1-quart baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water and bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until just barely set.
Just before serving, top with meringue made from remaining egg white, 2 tablespoons sugar and a few drops of almond extract.
Garnish with bits of red jelly.

title: cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together first 4 ingredients. Then add egg and vanilla to mixture.
Sift together the next 3 ingredients.
Add the last 5 ingredients.
Mix all together well. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Put cooked spaghetti, with bottle of Italian dressing poured over it, in a large bowl, in icebox to cool.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt all ingredients and then stir in crab meat.
Very rich, but delicious.

title: molded french cream(makes 8 servings)
directions: Mix sour cream and whipping cream in medium saucepan.
Beat on medium with electric mixer until blended.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Cook over low heat until warm.
Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add to cream mixture and remove from heat.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking pan. In a small bowl, mix the brown sugar, flour and walnuts.
Stir in melted margarine until well combined.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumbs. Pat remaining crumbs gently into pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together	and
bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover,
add
sprinkle of paprika and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: walnut delight
directions: Beat egg whites until slightly stiff. Add sugar, vanilla, baking powder, Ritz crackers and walnuts. Mix well and pour in greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for exactly 25 minutes. Allow pie to cool to room temperature, then cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Lightly butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a layer of whole graham crackers on bottom.
Top with half of the pudding mixture.
Add another layer of crackers and the rest of the pudding mixture. Cover with another layer of crackers.
Spread chocolate frosting on top of crackers.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheddar cheese spread
directions: Grate both cheeses.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish, put cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes at 325 degrees.
Serve with crackers.
Can be made in advance and frozen.

title: rubie allen's red slaw
directions: *For 1/2 cabbage or 1 small cabbage, use 1 heaping tablespoonful.

title: chocolate texas sheet cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Boil next 4 ingredients together. Pour liquid over dry ingredients and mix well, then mix baking soda with buttermilk.
Add to first ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
(Not a thick batter, watch closely).

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: The night before, grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put broken bread into baking dish.
Add the Smokie links or ham or browned sausage and shredded cheese.
Mix the eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt together and pour over the bread.
Let set all night in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hummingbird nectar
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Cool thoroughly.
Add food coloring if desired.
Pour into hummingbird feeder.
Can freeze extra and reheat later.
May adjust amounts but always use 1 part sugar to 4 parts water.
In Southeast, feeders are usually visited by hummingbirds from April until October.

title: russian tea
directions: Add cinnamon and cloves to water and bring to a boil.
Add tea bags and remove from heat.
Let steep 15 minutes.
In separate pot, mix and bring to a boil the following: orange juice, lemon juice, unsweetened pineapple juice and sugar.
Remove tea bags, cinnamon and cloves from 1st mixture and add to last mixture.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Drop cabbage into boiling salted water for a few minutes to soften leaves.
Combine beef, onion, rice, egg, salt and pepper and a couple tablespoons of tomato soup.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Brown beef in skillet; drain off grease. Empty into saucepan. Add Creole sauce, pepper, salt and chili powder. Let simmer 5 minutes. Add noodles. Empty into Pyrex dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: weight watcher's milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender; blend for 30 seconds.
Pour into a tall glass.
Delicious!

title: grilled salmon skillet
directions: Take one large salmon; cut in half to form a slab. Lay on grill with flame as low as possible. Coat fish with butter, then with liquid smoke. Add lemon pepper, crushed dill and garlic on top. Cook until well done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, chip dip and mustard.
Shred chipped beef.
Add 1/4 of the beef.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Use the rest of the beef to cover ball.
Chill and serve.

title: diabetic shrimp chowder
directions: Combine shrimp, celery and onion in a saucepan with enough water to cover (1 cup).
Simmer on low until vegetables are tender.
Add potatoes, milk and oleo.
Heat.
Season to taste. Yields 2 servings.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with softened cream cheese.
Add boiling water. Add cold water.
Beat slightly with egg beater.
Add crushed pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil cabbage until leaves are softened.
Cool.
Mix meat, eggs, rice, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Make sauce by putting white and brown sugar in pan with chopped onions.
Cook until sugar melts.
Add tomato sauce, lemon juice and ginger.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Place small amount of meat in each cabbage leaf. Fold up like an envelope.
Add cabbage rolls to sauce and bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours.
Turn off heat and leave in oven to cook slowly for one hour more.
Serve hot.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to manufacturer's instructions. Blend sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Toss lightly with apples. Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Combine butter, brown sugar and flour.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Cover with pastry top.
Cut slits in top.
Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: four bean salad
directions: Warm vinegars together and add sugar, salt, garlic and black pepper.
Add oil and mix.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight.

title: pecan haystacks
directions: Melt morsels in medium saucepan over low heat.
Turn off heat. Add pecans and noodles, stirring to coat well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: company meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into mound and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour catsup over top; continue cooking 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Double recipe will make 3 pies.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and cocoa just to a boil;
add in peanut butter and vanilla and stir thoroughly.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let sit until hardened. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: katie's pecan pralines
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients at high temperature for 5 minutes.
(You'll need a very large pot as the soda makes the mixture boil very high.)
Add the pecan pieces and the butter. Continue cooking and lower temperature to medium-high and stir often.
Be sure to scrape the bottom of the pot often.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Drop some of mixture into a cup of cold water and test with finger to see if it has hardened.
When this occurs, remove from fire and add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla extract.
Then begin stirring until it is ready to drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Check sides of pot by touching to see if mixture has semi-hardened and also mixture has thickened.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients listed 1 time.
Top with buttered crackers.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: party cheese wreath
directions: Beat Cheddar cheese and cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add juice, bell pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and ground pepper.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Place drinking glass in center of serving platter. Drop rounded tablespoons of mixture to form ring around glass just touching outer edge of glass. Smooth with spatula.
Remove glass. Garnish with chopped parsley and red pepper.
Serve with crackers.

title: cool party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook, peel and dice potatoes.
Mix with next 3 ingredients. Season with salt and pepper.
Spread mixture into greased casserole.
Top with olives, bacon and cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: madeline's broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 2-quart microwave-safe dish. Cover.
Microwave on High for about 10 minutes, depending on wattage of microwave whether more or less time is needed.
This can also be baked in regular oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Place breasts in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place broccoli spears and onion rings in boiling water.
Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender; drain off excess liquid.
Arrange broccoli over chicken, topping with onion rings.
Combine undiluted soup and milk, stirring until smooth.
Pour 1/2 mixture over vegetables, then top with cheese.
Pour rest of soup evenly over cheese.
Combine soft bread crumbs and butter, scatter them evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple slice dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients to well-beaten egg.
Combine this with pineapple juice; mix well.
Cook in a double boiler until clear. Then add butter.
Pour over sliced pineapple and top with grated cheese.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, 2 teaspoons salt, margarine, egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover bowl tightly with aluminum foil. Refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.

title: molded jello salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and jello in boiling water.
Cool and add rest of ingredients.
Set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Stir together bread and milk.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except filling.
Pat 1/2 of meat mixture in greased loaf pan. Cover with Cheese Filling.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Fill several loaf pans.
Bake at 345° for 1 hour.
(This is one I have made.)

title: my best fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, nuts and candied fruit with the egg mixture.
Put in tube pan in cold oven for 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water.
Add cream cheese, sour cream and butter.
Whip until smooth.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter, paprika and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, salt, black pepper and hamburger seasoning together.
Form meatballs.
Cook over low heat until done, stirring occasionally.

title: no bake crispy peanut butter balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, 1/2 cup cereal, milk powder and honey. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining cereal.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until onions are tender.
Add broth, water and Worcestershire.
Bring to boil; reduce cook for 25 minutes.
Spoon into crocks.
Place bread on top and sprinkle with Parmesan and top with Mozzarella.
Broil until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: mexican cheese squares
directions: Crumble cheese in pan.
Sprinkle chopped chiles on top.
In blender, mix milk, eggs and flour.
Pour over cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar, baby food and pineapple.
Heat until Jell-O and sugar are dissolved.
Do not boil.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cocktail salad(serves 12)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and juice.
Cool.
Mix milk, cottage cheese and mayonnaise together until smooth.
Add fruit cocktail. Pour into Jell-O and mix evenly.
Chill until set.
Add pecans on top.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients, except beef. Then add beef.
Marinate 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook on racks over baking pans at 175° for 5 to 6 hours, making sure slices are separated.

title: quick cash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: flavored ritz bits
directions: Put aluminum foil on cookie sheets.
Mix first 3 ingredients. Mix crackers with 1/2 of mixture and spread on cookie sheets. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes.
Mix in the other half of the mixture and continue baking for 1 hour, stirring again after 30 minutes.
(Total baking time: 2 hours.)

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until top is brown.

title: chocolate mound cake
directions: Add cake mix, 1/2 cup of sugar, oil and milk; beat well and bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn light bread
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: butter pecan loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
This makes 2 loaves.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out on wire rack.

title: dressed apricot salad
directions: Drain apricots; reserve juice.
Chop apricots.
Combine flour and sugar; stir into eggs.
Pour into top of double boiler; stir in lemon juice and reserved apricot juice.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool dressing thoroughly. Combine apricots, cheese and nuts; spread in shallow mold.
Pour dressing over top; chill thoroughly.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use for hot or cold tea.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut avocados in half.
Scoop avocados from shell; save shell. Mash avocados.
Add all ingredients.
Fill shells with avocado mixture.
Serve on lettuce leaf with taco chips.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients; blend well.
Makes two 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaves.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
Or makes three 7 1/2 x 3 1/3 x 2 1/4-inch loaves.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Grease and flour pans.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix well cake mix, water, eggs, sour cream and oil.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill bowl that your going to beat milk in.

title: peanut and celery soup
directions: Heat the margarine in the casserole pot and add the celery and onion.
Cook gently for 5 minutes.
Add the broth and the peanut butter.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat, cover and simmer gently for 30 minutes, until the celery is tender.
Cool the mixture a little, then blend until smooth.
Serves 4.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add wild rice and bring to a boil again.
Simmer until tender, stirring with a fork, until all of broth is absorbed.
Saute the celery, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Cook pork sausage.
Do not drain.
Combine rice, vegetables and pork.
Mix well and beat well.
Makes 6 cups.

title: desahtuk's grandmother's indian pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Stir cornmeal slowly into salted boiling water.
Return to a boil; reduce heat and cook slowly 2 1/2 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar, butter, eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well and pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with raisins and almonds.
Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm or cold, cut into small squares.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given. Chill 1 hour or overnight. Shape into strawberries, not too big. Roll in red sugar. Color sliced almonds green in a small amount of water with green food coloring. Stick two green almond slices in large end of strawberry for leaves. Or, dip large end of strawberry in lime gelatin or green sugar for stem.

title: wild rice supreme
directions: *Use seasoning packet and amount of water called for on box.

title: holiday banana pudding
directions: In bowl, combine milk and water. Mix with wire whisk. Add instant pudding. Mix well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart dish. Layer wafers and bananas. Repeat twice, ending with pudding. Cover. Chill.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Stir in flour and next 3 ingredients.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in soup; simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sour cream and heat throughly.
Do not boil.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until melted.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Add sour cream and nuts.
Pour into oiled baking dish.
Serve on lettuce with dollop of sour cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oatmeal cranberry white chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degree. In a medium bowl, beat butter and sugar with electric mixer till light and fluffy. Add eggs, mixing well. In separate bowl, combine oats, flour, soda and salt. Add to butter mixture slowly. Stir in cranberries and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10-12 minutes or till golden brown. Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: special potato salad
directions: In saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl combine vinegar, mustard, basil, pepper and salt; mix well.
Drain potatoes, cut into 1 inch chunks and add to vinegar and oil mixture while warm.
Toss to coat; cool.
In another bowl, combine yogurt, sour cream, and garlic salt.
Add onion, celery, bacon and eggs; mix well.
Add to potato mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill for several hours.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Slice cake or break in pieces and place in pan; pour and spread
pudding
over
cake, then spread pie filling over that. Refrigerate overnight or put in freezer for 1/2 hour.
Put Cool Whip over cake and serve.

title: easter cake
directions: Follow directions and bake for 20 minutes at 375° in greased jelly roll pan.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and grease a shallow baking pan.
Soak both kinds of bread in 1 cup water.
Chop onion and parsley fine. Mash soaked bread with fork.
Now, put meat in a mixing bowl, add bread, onion, parsley, cheese, slightly beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well and dump into baking pan.
Shape into loaf.
Dot top of loaf with margarine and bake for 30 minutes.
Then pour tomato sauce over meat, sprinkle with oregano and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: ruth's fudge
directions: Boil 4 1/2 minutes; pour over first ingredients.
Mix well. Add nuts; spread on greased cookie sheet.

title: jamaican jungle bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 8 ingredients. In a medium pan, mix bananas, pineapple, oil and eggs. Add all at once to oat mixture. Stir just until liquid is absorbed and mixture is thoroughly moistened (do not overmix). Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Loosen edges with a knife. Turn bread out on a cooling rack. Cool completely. Glaze, if desired.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients along with milk.
Add chopped fruit and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°. Makes 110 cookies.

title: chicken with capers
directions: Saute in a little oil on bottom of large pot the onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, garlic, paprika and parsley flakes until soft.
Add chicken; stir on high flame until it is all mixed up. Turn flame down to medium; simmer about 15 minutes.
Add capers and olives; cook for 20 minutes, then add tomato sauce, vinegar and bay leaf.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add celery; cook 20 minutes more, or until tender.
Stir up chicken a little throughout cooking.
Serve with rice.
Makes own gravy.

title: strata
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place 1/2 bread on bottom; layer with 1/2 the cheeses and 1/2 the cooked sausage.
Repeat. Beat eggs; add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over top. Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking at 350°, add cracker crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake approximately 45 minutes.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil. Cool. Marinate beef in mixture for a minimum of 4 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook and stir chicken in hot oil until lightly browned.
Stir in soup, milk, mustard and cheese; add broccoli and pimiento.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Then add dry ingredients, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
(Better if baked on aluminum foil.)

title: eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk for 2 minutes.
Fold in 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Using a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, layer graham crackers, pudding mixture, graham crackers, pudding, graham crackers.
A layer of crackers must be the top layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before frosting.

title: bacon-turkey salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Toss lettuce, bacon, tomato and turkey.
Garnish with egg slices.
Serve with Barbecue Dressing.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients, then put in refrigerator.
Keep tightly covered.
Take out as needed and knead with a little extra flour. Bake at 450° for about 10 or 15 minutes.

title: mama's fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Dip tomatoes in batter. Fry in 2-inches of hot oil (375°). Turn once during browning. Don't drain on paper; it makes them soggy.

title: lemon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Chill 6 to 8 hours.

title: hot lettuce dressing for two
directions: In a bowl combine egg, salt, flour, sugar, vinegar, Miracle Whip and water.
Sprinkle in some Hormel bacon bits.
Bring to a slow boil until thickened.
Pour over dandelion or lettuce.

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Remove and discard crusts from bread, if desired.
Butter bread; cube and place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle cheese, sausage, red pepper and onions in order over the bread.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add soup, milk, wine, mustard, and pepper.
Pour over bread mixture; cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 hour or until a knife comes out clean. Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine milk and cornmeal and cook together until thick.
Add the salt and the egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites and sugar.
Pour into buttered pan, bake 30 minutes in moderate oven.

title: "voithino me fasoulakia" - beef with green beans
directions: Heat oil and onion in a pot until lightly browned.
Add meat; stir until brown.
(Add water if it gets dry.)
Add tomato paste, salt and pepper; add enough water to cover meat.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
(If fresh beans, wash them and snap them in halves.) Put them over meat, then put chopped tomatoes over meat.
Add enough water to cover vegetables; cook until vegetables are done. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: beef and rice bake
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet; drain off excess fat.
Combine with soup mix, rice, boiling water and tomatoes.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables and soup and pour in Pyrex.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Cut bread into cubes and place on top of cheese.
Melt margarine and pour over bread.
Bake in a 325° oven until soup bubbles and bread is toasted.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and sugar.
Mix by hand.
Add flour; mix by hand and add other dry ingredients.
Mix by hand and fold in carrots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and 1/2 teaspoon sugar for 45 minutes.
Blend shortening with 1/2 cup sugar.
Add beaten egg with mixer until light.
Add salt, warm water and dissolved yeast. Mix well.
Add enough sifted flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out on board and knead until elastic to the touch, using up the rest of the flour.
(Perhaps a little more flour may be needed if dough feels sticky.)
Put the dough in a greased bowl in a warm place to double its bulk.
The dough may be kneaded down and shaped into rolls and baked or put in refrigerator for future use.

title: cucumber slaw
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice thinly into bowl; add salt so that each slice is lightly salted.
Soak overnight or for several hours in refrigerator.
Drain and rinse well (this procedure not necessary, but takes some of the strong flavor away).
Before serving, mix mayonnaise with sugar and vinegar.
Add to cucumbers and let stand for 1/2 hour or more before serving.

title: microwave tomato soup cake
directions: Beat eggs then add water, tomato soup and cake mix.
Grease microwave safe bundt pan and sprinkle 1 Tbsp. sugar to coat pan well.
Pour batter into bundt pan and microwave 9 minutes on medium power then 5 minuses on high power.

title: meat and cheese pie
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Add cheese, onion and meat.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test for doneness, knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: christmas relish
directions: Slice all vegetables into slices about 2-inches long.
Mix everything together in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into log.
Roll in pecans and parsley.
Serve with buffet rye crackers or king size Fritos.

title: cinnamon fluff
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Then add flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in alternately the sour milk.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Mix together the last 3 ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 9 servings.
Serve with lemon sauce or cinnamon flavored whipped cream.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vanilla and water, then gradually add to dry ingredients.
Dough is very thick.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chuck wagon soup
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water.
Saute hot dogs in butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, simmer 5 minutes.
Good with garden salad and hot rolls.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and store dry in jars or cans.
Makes great gifts.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble bacon.
Scramble eggs in hot skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When eggs are done, add remaining ingredients.
Heat shells for 1 minute in microwave. Place 1 heaping tablespoon of mixture on shell and roll.

title: panocha (candy)
directions: Boil first five ingredients to a soft ball stage (237°), stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and nuts. Set pan in cold water and start beating at once.
When mixture turns creamy and light, turn into buttered pan.
Cut in squares. If it hardens too soon, knead it soft again and put in pan.

title: sweet and sour neck bones
directions: Bring neck bones to a boil; rinse and put in roaster pan. Season with salt, pepper, garlic and onion.
Mix vinegar and brown sugar.
Pour over neck bones.
Cook covered until tender at 350°, approximately 2 hours.
Uncover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Slowly bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove whole spices and serve with orange slices.

title: cowboy biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and apples and set aside.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix well until batter is smooth.
Alternate batter, apples-cinnamon-sugar mixture in tube pan until all ingredients have been used.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix rest in order given.
Mold into 2 or 3 rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate until hard and cold.
Slice thin.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: sister sara's coconut custard pie
directions: Mix together sugar, egg yolks, bread, butter and coconut.
Add milk and stir well.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Fold in egg whites last.
Pour mixture into 2 (10-inch) pans lined with pastry.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with coconut, if desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Do not drain liquid from corn.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a large, greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.
(Done when knife comes out clean when inserted near center.)

title: lima beans casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crushed Ritz crackers or bread crumbs.
Pour 1 stick melted margarine on top.
Bake until bubbly in a 350° oven.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and milk; add lime juice gradually, beating until smooth.
Pour in pie shell.
Beat egg whites until soft and peaks form.
Spoon meringue over filling to edge.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes, until meringue is golden brown.
Cool before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Put nuts and fruit in large bowl.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Pour over nut mixture.
Mix well.
Beat eggs until foamy and add vanilla.
Stir into nut mixture.
Put in greased and lined pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 hours.
Cool.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Store in tight container or wrap in wine dipped cloth.
Makes 1 cake.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice and seasonings.
Add chicken, coating each piece well.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Roll chicken in crumbs; arrange in single layer in large shallow baking pan.
Melt butter and shortening; spoon half the mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Spoon remaining butter mixture over chicken; bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until chicken is tender and browned.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Bring soup mix and water to a boil. Add preserves and dressing mix.
Pour mixture over chicken and refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting often.

title: sauerkraut noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add sauerkraut and simmer until meat is tender. Add rest of ingredients and pour diluted soup over.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: mrs. krisher's sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients together; cream sugar and butter.
Add vanilla.
Make sweet milk by putting eggs, salt and then enough milk to equal 1 cup.
Mix all together.
Add raisins, if desired.
Put on greased cookie sheet by tablespoons. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Tastes better if you mix everything by hand.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in skillet and drain.
Pour over mixture of cornbread mix, eggs, milk and cream corn and cheese. Mix together.
Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Place several at a time in bag and shake.
Place pecans in bottom of a greased Bundt pan.
Layer biscuit pieces on top of pecans.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese bars
directions: Press 1 roll softened cookie dough on the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix crumbs and cheese into the margarine.
Take 1/2 crumb mixture out and spread remaining crumb mixture in pan.
Drain asparagus, saving liquid from 1 can.
Mix liquid with soup.
Lay asparagus over crumb mixture in baking dish.
Pour 1/2 liquid over it.
Top with remaining crumb mixture. Pour remaining liquid over top and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mama's oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add white and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and soda.
Stir in raisins, nuts, vanilla and cinnamon.
Make into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Bring brown sugar and margarine to a boil for 30 seconds, then add milk and vanilla.
After greasing a Bundt pan, pour in half of mixture.
Next, roll tubes of biscuits individually in sugar and cinnamon.
Place, end for end, in Bundt pan and pour rest of mixture on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Flip upside-down on plate.

title: armenian stew
directions: Cook meat and onions in oil until brown; drain.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, tomato sauce and 1 can of water.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over cracked wheat.

title: jon's mexican crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for crab meat. Lightly mix or toss in crabmeat and coat well. Chill for at least 2 hours. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook macaroni according to directions, omitting salt and fat. Drain well. Heat oil or shortening in large skillet on medium heat. Add onion and garlic and saute until tender. Add chicken and cook until no longer pink. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, ketchup, basil, oregano and salt. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Combine macaroni, broccoli and chicken mixture with 1/4 cup cheese. Stir well. Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: toutke pie
directions: Peel and cut potatoes.
Cook all ingredients together until meat is well done.
Drain off excess fat.
Put mixture into a large kettle with about 1/2 cup water.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt the butter in the microwave in a microwave-safe dish. Add the flour, salt and pepper and blend together.
Add the milk and return to the microwave.
Heat until very hot, not boiling. Add the cheese and heat in microwave until cheese is melted; do not boil.
Pour over the cooked macaroni.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup.
Pour into oblong dish and spoon soup over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: beets for meats
directions: Combine all ingredients in plastic container or jar and store in refrigerator for at least 8 hours before serving.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 12 casserole dish with Pam and pat out 1/3 of hamburger meat into bottom of pan. Then add a layer of onions and a layer of potatoes. Add 1/3 of soup mix. Continue to layer until all ingredients are used, ending with soup on top. Cover with foil and put in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours. Serve with a side salad.

title: cheddar batter bread
directions: Bake in a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan sprinkled with the 1 tablespoon cornmeal.

title: taters and franks
directions: In skillet, combine first 3 ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Drain.

title: fide's chicken flautas(taquitos)
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove the skin and debone.
Shred chicken.
In a large bowl, mix in all ingredients except for tortillas.
Set aside.
Warm up tortillas on top of a grill.
Once tortillas are warmed, fill each tortilla with the mix (about 3 tablespoons per tortilla).
Roll and deep fry until lightly brown and crunchy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients, adding bananas last.
Bake, in 2 loaf pans that have been sprayed with Pam, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
Wash and dice squash.
Cook in 1-inch of water with Worcestershire or soy sauce.
Cook at medium-high heat until almost done (about 10 to 15 minutes). Drain well.
Mix in onion, mayonnaise, egg and cheese.
Stir to mix together and pour into square 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Lay pads of butter onto top, then top with breadcrumbs.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion in 2 tablespoons margarine until brown and crumbly.
Combine with macaroni, catsup, bouillon, 1/2 cup cheese, parsley, pepper, cinnamon and 2 teaspoons salt.
Turn into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, sprayed.
Heat remaining 6 tablespoons butter; add flour and cook until bubbly, gradually stir in milk.
Add remaining 1 teaspoon salt and mustard.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Gradually stir the hot mixture into eggs.
Pour over macaroni mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Place rice in bottom of 4-cup casserole dish. Pour tomatoes over rice. Place meat on top of rice/tomato mixture. Cover dish. Microwave 14 to 15 minutes on High. Check after 8 minutes as microwaves are different. Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: beef-n-beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, drain. Add pork-n-beans, stir. Add cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste. Simmer down until just a little liquid is left (do not let dry out). Add a pinch of crushed red pepper if desired. Serve.

title: iron skillet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together like making cornbread.
Put in a greased and floured iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until done.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a container.
Makes lots of bubbles.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in margarine until transparent. Add sliced squash and let cook in its own liquid.
Combine beaten eggs, sugar, one cup grated cheese and green chiles.
Pour over squash onion mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: cobbler mix
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk together.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Then pour pie filling or fresh fruit over batter.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan melt peanut butter chips in 1 cup condensed milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir.
Remove from heat.
Spread onto wax paper-lined 11 x 7-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt cheese, butter and milk over low heat.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix well the lemon concentrate, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Pour into 2 graham pie shells.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Mix and bake as you would any other pound cake.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar.
Add flour, mix well.
Add vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Roll into small balls, a little bit smaller than a quarter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: s & w chess pie(old charlotte)
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, corn meal, flour, salt and nutmeg until light.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Add milk and mix well. Let stand 30 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes or until firm.
Very good.

title: sugarless spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is almost gone.
Mix applesauce, eggs, margarine, sweetener, oats and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potluck baked beans
directions: Mix together all beans carefully in bowl.
Boil bacon, onion, catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard for 5 minutes.
Pour boiled sauce over beans, then put in large 9 x 14-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Layer the peas, carrots, potatoes and onion in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order.
Combine the soup and water.
Pour over layers. Brown the pork chops quickly. Salt and pepper to taste.
Put pork chops on top and press down.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° until potatoes and carrots are done. Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake(very good)
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or long cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: seafood okra gumbo
directions: Saute seasonings in butter until wilted.
Add okra and saute about 15-20 minutes longer.
Add brown flour.
Mixture will be pasty.
Add tomatoes and broth and enough water to make about 3 quarts liquid.
Add shrimp, sausage, and gumbo crabs (if using crabmeat wait to add until about 15 minutes before serving).
Cook about 45 minutes on medium heat.
Season to taste.
Serve with rice.

title: rice cheese souffle
directions: Combine butter, flour and milk.
Cook over hot water until smooth and thick.
Add well beaten egg yolks and rice.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add cheese.
Mix until cheese is melted.
Season with salt and cayenne.
Cool.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into well-oiled casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Moisten the bread crumbs with water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
If too thick, you may add more water until mixture pours easily into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned and set.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add egg, flour, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add mashed bananas, salt and sour cream.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: southern sweet potato delight
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with the following topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil and fry.
Yields 18 medium fritters.

title: 7-can soup
directions: Pour all 7 cans of vegetables and beans into saucepan and heat.

title: smoky links
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir.
Cook on medium for 5 hours.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring peanut butter, water and margarine to a rapid boil. Pour over flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Mix and add the eggs and buttermilk.
Pour batter into a greased sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: connie's cheese ball
directions: Soften.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Form into ball and chill.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and both sugars.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Set 1 cup crumb mixture aside.
Press remainder on the bottom and sides of 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients (except crumb mixture) in same bowl.
Pour into baking dish with crumb mixture. Bake for 55 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream
together
margarine
and sugar.	Add
egg,
beat until creamy.
Grate unpared apples; add to the mixture.	Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add
to
the mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan
and
bake
at 400° about 30 minutes (this is a rather stiff batter).

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Slice zucchini in long slices.
Bring to boil and cook about 5 minutes; drain.
In a 9 x 14 x 2-inch pan, spoon a thin layer of sauce.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of bread crumbs.
Arrange layer of zucchini to cover bottom completely.
Combine Ricotta, eggs, parsley, seasonings, 1/2 Parmesan and 1/2 remaining crumbs.
Spoon this mixture over zucchini.
Sprinkle 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and repeat layers, ending with crumbs and Parmesan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat cream cheese and tomato soup until melted; add Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup water.
Stir in all ingredients, then gelatine.
Pour in mold, then refrigerate until set.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix brown sugar and whipping cream.
Microwave (without stirring) for 13 minutes.
Add butter and pecans.
Drop by tablespoons onto foil.

title: cornbread
directions: Moderately grease large cast-iron skillet.
Measure cornmeal, flour and sugar into large bowl.
Beat egg with fork (using small circular motion).
Add to cornmeal mixture.
Add buttermilk.
Beat mixture with a spoon.
Add melted butter.
Stir.
Pour into pan. Cook at 450° to 475° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut honey balls
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and shape into balls, using teaspoons for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 18 minutes, until golden brown.
If desired, dip warm cookies in pineapple glaze.
Let stand one hour before storing.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 325° for 60 to 90 minutes, until firm.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with croutons.
Melt the butter and pour over the croutons.
Layer the sausage and mushrooms; cover with cheese.
Mix in a blender the milk, eggs, soup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture over the items in the 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° uncovered.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Stir soda into buttermilk, set aside.
Add eggs and bananas to sugar mixture.
Alternately add buttermilk mixture and flour.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees, if baked in a loaf pan about 1 hour, or in a layer pan for 30 minutes.

title: german fried potatoes
directions: Chop and parboil potatoes; drain.
Add all ingredients in small skillet and cook over medium heat, stirring often.
When potatoes are tender and falling apart, dish is ready.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Place flour
and
salt in bowl.
Stir in water for soft dough. Knead
until
elastic
but not sticky.
Form into golf size balls.
Dip
into flour one at a time.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until meat is tender (not too brown).
Drain.
Add all other ingredients, except noodles.
Mix well.
Fold in noodles very carefully.
Pour in ungreased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° with cover for about 1 hour.
Take out of oven.
Put cheese on top and place back in oven without the cover.
Let cheese melt and lightly brown.
Freezes well.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator or bake right away.
Do not let rise before you bake them.
Bake in a 425° oven until golden brown.

title: salsa
directions: Combine ingredients and let sit for 12 hours. Serve with corn tortillas or corn chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Mix all other ingredients, except the cheese. Add margarine and mix well. Place in baking dish; top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and sausage and drain.
Add chopped onion and all spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook egg dumplings according to package directions.
Drain water.
Mix meat mixture, half of grated cheese and soups.
Add can of water.
Mix well.
Place in large dish and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cornbread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Stir in the cheese.
Combine milk and eggs.
Add to mixture, mixing just until moist.

title: chief's border burrito
directions: Cook steak medium-rare; let cool and cut into small pieces. Put approximately 3 tablespoons of meat into flour tortilla.
Add 1 tablespoon onion and 1 tablespoon olives.
Pour small amount of sauce onto mixture and sprinkle cheese into mixture.
Roll tortilla.
Pour sauce on top.
Add olives, onion and cheese.
Put into microwave for 1 minute.
Put sour cream and tomatoes on top. Serve hot.
Makes 12.

title: chicken bavarian
directions: Mix first six ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay the pieces of chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup mix over this.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Add almonds over top after baking.

title: homemade guacamole
directions: Chop and blend together with spoon.
Refrigerate before serving.
(Does not keep well overnight.)

title: danish pot roast
directions: Dredge pot roast with flour and brown on all sides in hot fat. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
Add vinegar and hot water.
Cover tightly.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours, adding water, if necessary.
Thicken the liquid for gravy by beating 3 tablespoons flour with cold water until smooth.
Bring liquid to boiling point.
(Add water to make 1 1/2 cups.)
Add gravy thickening, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add potato chips and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place salmon in greased casserole dish. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Melt butter in pan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Gradually add milk until blended.
Combine crumbs and melted butter.
Mix.
Sprinkle evenly over salmon mixture.
Cover.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Will fall slightly when uncovered.

title: coconut fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add fruit cake mix, coconut, raisins and nuts; mix well.
In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and extract; mix well. Stir in the flour mixture alternately with orange juice.
Pack into a greased 10-inch tube pan.

title: strawberry-filled french toast
directions: Spread cream cheese on 6 of the bread slices.
Spread jam over the cream cheese.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Cut diagonally.
Beat together milk, vanilla and nutmeg in a shallow bowl.
Dip each triangle in egg mixture.
Fry in margarine. When brown on first side, turn over and fry on the other side until brown.
Serve with maple syrup.
Garnish with fresh fruit.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix all and bake at 300° for about 50 minutes.

title: potato icebox rolls
directions: Mix yeast with potato water, then add sugar, shortening, salt, eggs and potatoes.
Add mixture to 6 1/2 cups flour and mix well. Then add the cup of warm water.
Work well and knead about 10 to 15 minutes, adding the remaining cup of flour as necessary.
Let rise in greased container.
Grease top of dough.
Push down and cover well and refrigerate until needed.
Remove from refrigerator and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno-potato soup
directions: In large stock pot, saute onion in butter or margarine until just tender.
Add potatoes, chicken broth and comino.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.
When done; add jalapenos, soda and evaporated milk. Coarsely mash potatoes with a potato masher.
Stir well and taste for salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Garnish with dollop of sour cream and chopped green onions.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: sarah's dish
directions: Mix together beans and corn.
Spread on bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.

title: iowa corn chowder
directions: Chop bacon and cook in soup pan until crispy.
Do not drain. Add onions and saute until soft.
Add potatoes and 2 cups of the water; salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in corn with liquid.
Blend the flour with the remaining water and stir into chowder.
Cook, stirring constantly, until chowder thickens and bubbles, about 3 minutes. Ready to serve.

title: "shrooms"
directions: Wash and stem mushrooms.
Place upside down on cookie sheet. Place 1 teaspoon of cream cheese in each cap.
Place 1/4 teaspoon Ortega chilies on each (on top of cream cheese). Pour melted butter over all.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup very warm water in glass measuring cup.
In large bowl, stir flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and yeast mixture until blended.
Cover bowl with waxed paper; let dough stand for 5 minutes.
Lightly brush pizza pan with salad oil and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Pat dough onto pizza pan, shaping a ridge around edge of pan.
Put on pizza ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot crumb bars
directions: Combine cake mix, cracker crumbs, cinnamon and butter until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Add egg to remainder and mix until well blended.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°, until lightly golden.

title: potato salad with shrimp
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Season to your liking with black pepper and salt.
Heat skillet with oil.
Add shrimp.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cook crumbled sausage until done.
Spread each slice of bread with oleo and cut into cubes.
Place cubes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with cooked sausage.
Top with cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and mustard; beat and mix thoroughly.
Pour over top of cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to use, set pan out and bring to room temperature.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; blend and beat eggs into mixture.
Add sifted flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add carrots.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spread on layers.

title: dumb bunny cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place peaches with juice in pan. Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over cake mix.
Melt butter and drizzle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter or margarine.

title: potato sausage
directions: Run meat, potatoes and onions through grinder.
Add seasoning and mix well with meat mixture.
Rinse casings well and cut into 24 inch lengths for easy handling.
Stuff with mixture, leaving 1-inch for expansion.
Do not tie ends.
Poke a few holes in each ring. Place in a large roaster and cover with water.
Simmer uncovered 40 minutes.
Serve.

title: easy chocolate mousse
directions: Blend all in blender on high for 2 minutes.
Pour
into 4 dessert cups, top with foil and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until creamy.
Then blend in strawberries, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Pour into 9-inch pan.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: adobo
directions: Place all ingredients, except chicken, in a pot and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add chicken and simmer for another 15 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Continue to simmer, uncovered, until liquid is reduced to about 1/4 cup.
Serve hot over white rice.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Recipe can easily be doubled for use in various ways as Cinnamon Rolls, coffee cake, stollen, orange-Danish, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. After chicken has cooked, remove skin & bones. Cut chicken into bite size pieces & put in bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Pour cans of soup over chicken. In separate bowl, mix together stuffing & broth; then spread this mixture over the chicken & soup. Pour milk evenly over the stuffing mix. Cover 9 X 13 pan with foil & bake for 45 minutes. Remove foil & bake for another 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 425° until light brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: cabbage lemon salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, pouring salad oil over all to coat.
Then add salt, mustard seed and celery seed.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add cooked hamburg.
Pour into a greased pie plate.
Add cheese on top.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: honey roast cereal
directions: Melt butter and honey in large bowl in microwave.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Allow to cool completely, stirring to break up.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water and place in refrigerator until thick, but not congealed.
