Mix cream cheese with cherry juice. Fold in remainder of ingredients and chill.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add butter, 1/3 cup buttermilk and mashed bananas; beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and remaining 1/3 cup buttermilk; beat 2 minutes more.
Fold in nuts. Pour into layer pans and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar, banana and butter icing.

title: ba-ba ganouch
directions: Microwave eggplants on High for 10 to 11 minutes or until very soft.
Peel eggplants and put into blender.
Add garlic, lemon juice and sesame paste.
Blend on high speed until well mixed. Chill 2 hours before serving.
Serve as a dip with wedges of pita bread stuffed with sliced tomato.

title: easy chocolate toffee wafer candy
directions: Line a cookie sheet with buttered foil, then crackers.
In heavy saucepan, melt butter and sugar together; bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour hot butter mixture over crackers evenly.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, then spread chocolate evenly over candy.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until firm; break into pieces.

title: hot chicken with cashews(serves 4)
directions: Combine chicken, egg white, 3 teaspoons cornstarch and 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Mix well and refrigerate for one hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put half of the mixture into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix sugar
and cinnamon. Sprinkle half over batter and swirl in with fork.
Pour rest of batter in and top with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Swirl with fork.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: indian relish
directions: Finely chop tomatoes, apples and onions.
Put in a large saucepan.
Blend in sugar, vinegar, salt and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly, uncovered, until thick, about 2 or 3 hours.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yields 8 pints.

title: one dish supper treat
directions: Brown together beef or turkey and onion.
Add
corn and cream of potato soup.
Mix well and put into baking
dish
or pan.
Pour cornbread mixture over top and bake until cornbread is browned.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix crust ingredients well.
Pat in bottom of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: easy chicken dinner!
directions: Spray bottom of pan with Pam or nonstick oil.
Place chicken breast on bottom of pan.
(Mix together 1 can cream of chicken soup with 1/4 cup milk.)

title: parmesan primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package, drain.
In large skillet, melt oleo and cook broccoli and mushrooms until tender.
Add hot spaghetti and remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: april-fool carrots
directions: Place cream cheese in small bowl; let stand for 30 minutes at room temperature to soften.
Add Cheddar and honey to cream cheese. Mix on medium speed until blended.
Stir in 1/2 of shredded carrot. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 2 1/2-inch logs, tapered at one end to look like a carrot.
Spread remaining carrot on wax paper.
Roll each "cheese" carrot in shredded carrot to coat. Store in airtight container in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours.
Just before serving, insert parsley sprig in top of carrot.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss, chill and serve.

title: pear salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and juice from pears.
Let nearly congeal.
Add cream cheese, pears (blended) and nuts (chopped fine).
Fold in Dream Whip.
Refrigerate.
This may be made in a blender.

title: "men like it" salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Soften cream cheese and blend into pineapple.
Add celery and nuts.
When jello slightly congeals, add other ingredients and refrigerate until firm.

title: pudding dessert(any kind)
directions: Combine the oleo, flour and nuts; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburg; drain off fat.
Add all ingredients together; mix.
Put in casserole and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: terrific chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy or for 11 to 13 for crispy.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add part of milk to dissolve, then add egg yolks and rest of milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and coconut. Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue and place in 400° oven. Brown egg whites about 5 minutes; coconut may be sprinkled on top of egg whites before browning.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together; set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add flour mixture, cinnamon and vanilla; mix well.
Add apples and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into greased tube pan, Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: my mom's cherry crumble
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and crumble with pastry blender. Put half in bottom of 9 x 12 baking pan.
Cover with cherry pie filling. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and pat down.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown and filling is bubbling, about 40 minutes.
Mom served this to many hungry students and I have used it many times.
Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: In greased 2-quart casserole, add layers as given:
rice and corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix tomato paste and water and pour over all.
Add onion and chopped green pepper.
Add ground beef.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add second can of tomato paste mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Cover with strips of bacon.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable confetti
directions: Mix salt and pepper with vegetables.
Pour into buttered casserole.
In a separate bowl, mix melted butter with bread crumbs.
Mix 3/4 of buttered crumbs with the vegetables.
Add water and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° until vegetables are tender.

title: asian asparagus salad with pecans
directions: Bring a medium sauce pan of water to boil, and cook the asparagus until tender but crisp.
Drain and briefly run under cool water.
In a large ziploc bag, mix the rice vinegar, soy sauce, vegetable oil, sugar, salt, and pepper.
Seal the asparagus in the bag.
Marinate for 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Sprinkle the marinated asparagus with pecans and green onions to serve.

title: mound candy
directions: Put in big pan and work real well with hand, then press tight in greased Pyrex long dish.
Chill overnight.

title: pasta with pesto sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Mix with cooked, drained pasta.
Serve.

title: spiced nuts
directions: In a large frying pan, bring to a boil the sugar, water, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Mix thoroughly and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir until cool.
Spread and separate on waxed paper.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add egg and almond extract.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Dot with red food coloring.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour 2 cans sweetened condensed milk over mixture. Spread in a shallow pan (1-inch thickness) that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes. Cool slightly and cut in 1-inch squares.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Measure dry ingredients together.
Add zucchini, onion and cheese.
Beat eggs and add oil.
Mix dry and wet ingredients. Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side down. Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Remove chicken from dish.

title: aunt elsie's pecan pie
directions: Cook sugar and syrup until mixture thickens.
Beat eggs, without separating, and slowly add hot syrup to eggs, beating constantly. Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pour soup in small pan; add milk, water, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Put on stove and heat.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and add slices of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, vanilla, dates and nuts.
Pack in loaf pan.
Bake at 250° for approximately 2 hours.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Good with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, spray bundt pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes, cool in pan 1 hour. Invert onto serving plate and dust with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: velleggia's house dressing
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil and continue to beat until it gets thick. Add spices and vinegar and mix completely.
Top lettuce with dressing (coat evenly).
Sprinkle cheese (to taste) over coated lettuce and toss.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hello dolly's(cookies)
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer graham crackers in bottom of dish, then pecans, then coconut, then chocolate chips. Pour can of milk over entire pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chewy bread
directions: Blend sugar and butter;
add eggs one at a time.
Then blend by hand (this is important) the flour into mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until a tooth pick comes out clean.

title: chile noodles
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet until done and add onion, tomato sauce or tomatoes and green chilies.
In a separate pan cook noodles.
Drain and add to chile mixture.
Top mixture with grated cheese and put in hot oven until cheese mixture is melted.

title: soup respee
directions: Cook butter beans until tender.
Drain; add to mixture.
Cook 30 minutes.
Seal.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cover marshmallows with sweet potatoes, forming balls.
Place in shallow dish and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients. Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Yield: 2 pies.

title: nut kipelechen
directions: Mix all ingredients together for filling.

title: calas
directions: Place soft rice in a bowl.
Add eggs, flour, salt and nutmeg. Beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoon in deep, hot fat and fry golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Add 3 tablespoons flour; cook until bubbly. Add 2 cups milk; mix well and stir until boils; boil for 1 minute. Add 1 can chicken broth.
Add Velveeta; let melt.
Add 1/2 cup cooked carrots, diced onions and chopped celery or add 2 cups of cooked vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, etc.).

title: butterscotch-coconut squares
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift with baking powder and salt. Cream shortening; add sugar and mix well.
Add egg and vanilla, beat well.
Mix in flour mixture and 1 cup coconut.
Spread in a well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix together 1/2 cup coconut, butter and granulated sugar.
Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35
minutes.
Cut into squares while warm. Cool in pan.
Makes 16 squares.

title: chicken casserole with stuffing
directions: Mix broth and soup together.
Grease sides and bottom of casserole dish with butter.
Make a layer of stuffing, layer of chicken and layer of soup/broth mixture.
Pour melted butter over broth mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter in mixing bowl.
Add peanut butter, crumbs and powdered sugar.
Smooth into cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips. Pour and smooth over top of mixture.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: key lime cream cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spread the coconut in a 9-inch pie plate. Bake until it is light gold, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring several times so it colors evenly.
Cool slightly, then transfer to a food processor.
Add cookies and process until they are crumbled.
Add the melted butter and mix well.
Press crumb mixture into bottom and sides of pie plate.
Bake until set, about 8 minutes; cool completely on wire rack before filling.

title: vodka rigatoni
directions: Cook bacon until crispy.
Add onions and peppers. Saute until caramelized.
Add garlic, tomatoes and vodka.
Simmer about 30 minutes to reduce.
Add cream and basil.
Pour over pasta.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Cut up round steak into individual pieces.
Mix soup mix, water,
mushrooms and soup into a crock-pot.
Place meat in and stir until meat is coated.
Allow to cook on low in crock-pot for 6 hours.

title: green beans au gratin
directions: Drain beans and save liquid.
Fry bacon; drain skillet.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Add milk and bean liquid.
Stir constantly over low heat until thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes, uncovered, until crumbs are browned.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Serve hot.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Melt butter
and add crushed cracker crumbs.
Press into a glass baking dish.
Bake
minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat ice cream and milk together until
it
thickens
like milk shakes. Add pudding mix.
Pour over crumb layer.
The
top
may
be garnished with reserved crumbs or whipped cream.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in two round pans.
Make your cake in a punch bowl. Slice cake in half, making 4.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Shake flour, gravy mix, garlic powder and water in a 14 x 20-inch oven baking bag.
Squeeze bag to blend well.
Sprinkle seasoned salt and pepper over chicken.
Place in bag.
Place carrots and celery around chicken.
Close bag. Cut six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag.
Bake until chicken is tender, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix
and
press
first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat together with mixer and add red food coloring to desired shade of pink.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased baking dish. Top with 1/2 package shredded Cheddar cheese or Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese mix and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Serve warm with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: When mixed, take bits of dough and roll into balls.
Press flat with fork (crisscross).
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: southern barbecued chicken
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients except chicken, broil or grill 25 to 30 minutes; turning once, brush with ketchup mixture. Cook an additional
5 to 10 more
minutes or until chicken is done and tender.
While cooking brush with ketchup mixture until chicken is done.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan, line pan with biscuits and pinch to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: sugar popcorn
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thin string drops from spoon.
Pour onto unsalted popcorn; stir constantly.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off grease.
Place meat mixture in large pan or crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook slowly for 4 to 5 hours, covered.
Remove bay leaves and garlic before serving.
Serve on bed of spaghetti and top with grated cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Form a ball and roll in nuts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form balls.
Press down with floured fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes in their jackets until tender.
Peel and slice.
In a flat buttered 3-quart casserole, layer potato slices and season with salt and pepper.
Saute bell pepper and onions in 1/2 cup oleo until tender.
In saucepan, combine flour and 1/2 oleo and stir until bubbly.
Add milk and cheeses and stir over medium heat until cheese melts.
Add onion mixture and pimientos and blend well.
Pour over potatoes and bake for 45 minutes.
This is best when assembled the day before.

title: cheese filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package directions for about 10 minutes.
Drain well.
(Cool in a single layer on wax paper or aluminum foil to prevent sticking together.)
Mix together cheeses, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Spread a thin layer of sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place the shells, open side down, in a single layer in the pan.
Cover with about 2 cups of the sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake, covered, with aluminum foil at 350° for about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with shells.
Fills about 36 shells.

title: creamy orange-pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juices.
Add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boil, add boiling liquid to gelatin and cream cheese. Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
Whip cream.
Fold cream, grated carrot and pineapple to cooled gelatin.
Pour into individual or single mold. Chill until firm.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Grind cranberries and add sugar. Grind apple, orange (peel too) and nuts.
Add to cranberries, then add jello.
Just before serving, stir in Cool Whip.
Very good!

title: rechandle's wedding punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with sugar in ginger ale.
Mix all ingredients, except sherbet.
Chill.
After chilled and before serving, add 2 quarts of orange sherbet for foam and decorations.
At Christmas, use lime sherbet and lime Kool-Aid.

title: spicy chicken nacho bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place chips in glass baking dish.
Mix beans, 1 cup cheese and salsa until blended.
Spread evenly over chips.
Mix chicken and seasoning; sprinkle over bean mixture. Top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with tomato.
Makes 8 appetizers or 4 main dish servings.
Ten minutes to prep; 10 minutes to cook.

title: cranberry-raspberry iced tea
directions: Mix tea and juice.
Pour over ice.
Top with raspberries. Garnish with fresh mint, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.

Sift flour and baking powder and add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add flavorings. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 to1 1/4 hours.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apple cubes with sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add celery and nuts.
Fold mayonnaise into whipped cream.
Gently fold into apple mixture.
Chill.

title: baked fruit
directions: Mix, cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350° in Pam-sprayed pan.
Use only the amounts specified even though packages may be larger.
Better if fruit is cut into pieces.
Serve slightly warm or at room temperature.

title: gingerbread house cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg, molasses and vinegar. Sift together dry ingredients; blend in.
Preheat oven to 375°. Roll dough on lightly floured surface.
Cut into house shapes. Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool.
Decorate with icing and candies.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: biscuits
directions: Use hands and rub shortening into all dry ingredients until it looks like cornmeal.
Add milk and stir until dough leaves sides of bowl.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients at high speed with mixer then stir in 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup raisins, optional.
Bake in greased tube pan approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
May also use greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour or 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: lo-cal tuna dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, horseradish, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce in medium bowl; stir well.
Add onion, celery and green pepper; stir well.
Stir in tuna.
Cover and chill. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Yield:
1 3/4 cups.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken.
Cover with soup and milk. Mix
stuffing
with
broth.
Saute onions and celery in butter for 5 minutes.
Mix with stuffing and broth and sprinkle over top of casserole.	Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package except use whole eggs plus 1/2 can Angel Flake coconut.
When cake is done, punch holes in top of cake while still hot and pour 2/3 can cream of coconut on cake.
When cake is cooled, mix the Cool Whip, rest of cream of coconut and remainder of Angel Flake coconut for cake topping.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add green onions and beat well.
Spread on tortilla shells.
Top with ham and celery to desired thickness. Roll up like a jelly roll and wrap in aluminum foil.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and put a toothpick through to secure.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Cream until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough.

title: corn casserole
directions: Pour corn into pan.
Cook until water is gone.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding(serves 12)
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the corn, sugar, milk, margarine, eggs, salt and spice.
Pour into casserole; bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.
Do not overcook.
If left in oven too long, the pudding will weep, that is liquid will run out of it.

title: christmas stollen
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour; add milk, sugar, salt, egg, shortening and half the flour to yeast.
Mix with spoon until smooth.
Add chopped almonds, citron, cherries, raisins and lemon rind.
Mix well.
Add enough of the remaining flour to handle easily.

title: ruben's bacon dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients up to the bacon and let stand.
Dice and fry the bacon and drain all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Mix with other ingredients.
Toss with lettuce or fresh spinach, sliced onions, optional.

title: tomato marinade
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Pour marinade over tomatoes and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve.

title: aunt deb's muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add wheat germ and brewer's yeast.
Add dry ingredients alternately with mashed bananas.
Bake as mini muffins 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread the sliced apples in a greased 8-inch square pan. Combine brown sugar, flour, margarine and cinnamon.
This mixture will be sort of dry.
Crumble this mixture over the top of the apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: easy rolls
directions: Put mashed potatoes into a bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and scalded milk; let stand until cold.
Add yeast, beaten eggs and flour; knead slightly until smooth.
Place in refrigerator to rise gradually.

title: penuche squares
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add beaten eggs; beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture. Add vanilla, then pecans.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Since ovens vary, check in 15 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Walnuts may be used.
Batter will be thick.

title: refreshing "salad"
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello.
Add Cool Whip.
Then mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Chill Pet milk good.
Whip milk until thick.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add strawberries; mix well.
Put a layer of wafers in a pie plate and then a layer of strawberry filling.
Continue until all is used, ending with strawberry filling.
Put in freezer.
Set out about 15 minutes before serving.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugar very well. Add eggs (well beaten).
Add milk and flour. Beat 4 minutes.
Fold in flavoring. Start in cold oven. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: susan's fresh apple mini chip cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, apple juice and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Add flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon until smooth. Add apples, 1 cup chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until mixed well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 9-inch pans.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Defrost artichoke hearts, pat dry and cut in half.
Blend all ingredients together and pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in shortening or Pam.
Add 1 cup water, bouillon cube and 1/4 teaspoon salt; mix well.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch; add reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; add sauce and pork.
Mix well.
Stir in pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook about 3 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown meat; add celery and onions and cook until vegetables are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Save 1/4 cup noodles to cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork steak baked with fruit and carrots
directions: Sprinkle steaks with salt and pepper; dust with flour.
Brown on both sides in a skillet in which you have rendered out a little of the fat on the steaks.
Place in a utility pan or shallow baking dish.
Place a slice of pineapple on top of each steak, and put a prune in the center of each pineapple slice.
Arrange the sliced carrots around the steaks.
Pour in the water and cover.
Bake at 300° (slow oven) for 1 1/2 hours or until steaks are tender and well done.

title: low-fat mexican casserole
directions: Boil chicken, onion and pepper.
Debone chicken.

Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam and place a layer of tortillas to cover pan. Spread chicken and vegetables over tortillas, then layer soup, picante sauce, another layer of tortillas and top with cheese. Cook at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: melissa's peanut brittle(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix sugar, karo and water.
Cook until temperature reaches 275 degrees on candy thermometer.
Add peanuts and margarine. Cook until lightly brown.
Quickly add soda and salt.
Beat well to mix and pour into well buttered pan or large cookie sheet.

title: tofu bque
directions: Coarsely grind tofu in food processor.
Saute garlic in olive oil.
Stir in tofu.
Add soy sauce, tomato puree and paprika. Heat on low for no more than 5 minutes.
(Tofu releases moisture if cooked too long!)
Tasty on toasted wheat bread and served with black olives!

title: crunchy aspic
directions: Combine the cold water, sugar, vinegar and salt and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and stir in gelatine until dissolved.
Add onion and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until mixture slightly thickens, then add chilled asparagus, pimiento, water chestnuts and celery.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serve on watercress with dressing of mayonnaise, sour cream and a little curry.

title: tuna fish pie
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter until soft; add flour and blend.
Add milk and salt.
Boil 2 minutes, being careful not to burn.
Add tuna and lemon juice.
Put in baking dish.
Add Cheese Rolls on top of mixture and bake in oven at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, green chilies and Jack cheese and set aside 4 cups.
To the remainder, add the chicken, olives and green onions.
Put the mixture with chicken in each tortilla.
Roll up and place in baking dish (9 in each dish).
Pour 2 cups of the set aside mixture over the top of each dish.
Cover with cheddar cheese.

title: bacon-wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, ginger, garlic, mustard and brown sugar in shallow dish to make marinade. Wrap each water chestnut with a piece of bacon and secure with toothpick. Put in marinade and let stand for 1 hour at room temperature. Drain marinade.

title: herb butter
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Remove from refrigerator a few minutes before serving.
Yield 3/4 c.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in 1 quart of water.
Add juices, then add enough water to make 3 gallons of punch.
Freeze in gallon containers.
Remove from freezer 4 or 5 hours before serving; add 1 ginger ale to each gallon and serve slushy.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Brown sausage.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Mix rice, meat mixture, soup and mushrooms together and place in a casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
An optional garnish is olives, either green or black.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix the cabbage, carrots, onion, celery and green pepper well. Boil the vinegar, oil, salt, sugar and celery seed for 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour over vegetable mixture while hot.
Weight down and let stand until salad is cold.
Refrigerate for several hours. Divide into containers and store in refrigerator or freezer.
Will keep 3 weeks or more in refrigerator and indefinitely in freezer.

title: crab-cheese mix
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz, crabmeat, butter and Worcestershire sauce. Split English muffins. Spread with mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: How To Cook:
Without paring, boil potatoes 30 to 35 minutes. When tender, drain and slip off skins.
To bake: Scrub, then dry. Rub with a little vegetable oil.
Bake (large) at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tomatoes and lemon broccoli
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of lower stalks.
Cut into spears. Arrange broccoli in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Place broccoli in a serving bowl; add tomatoes. Combine lemon rind and next 3 ingredients; stir well. Drizzle over broccoli mixture; toss gently.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In small pan, combine beaten egg yolks, sugar, 2 tablespoons pineapple juice, butter and salt; stirring constantly on low heat until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, let cool slightly.
Beat cream until whipped.

title: chili beans
directions: Soak beans overnight or cover with hot water and soak for 2 hours.
Bring to boil and then add the bacon, brown sugar, thyme, half of the chopped onions and garlic.
Simmer until beans are tender.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat.
Bring Coca-Cola to a boil with cocoa and add to butter mixture.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, flour, baking soda and marshmallows last.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Ice while cake is hot.

title: apricot cake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup apricot nectar.
Mix and bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour reserved nectar over hot cake.

title: butter baked chicken and gravy
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Dip chicken in 1/2 cup Pet milk.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put chicken in skin side down.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Pour around chicken the soup, 3/4 cup Pet milk and water.
Bake 30 minutes more or until drumsticks are done.
Remove chicken.
Stir gravy well.

title: glorified chocolate cake
directions: Bake any chocolate cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let partially cool.
Poke holes all over cake.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and butterscotch topping over cake so it soaks into holes.
When entirely cool, cover with Cool Whip mixed with 2 crushed Heath bars.

title: foil wrapped dinner
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and make into 5 to 6 hamburger patties.
Cut large pieces of foil.
Place each patty in a piece of foil.
Close foil and begin to broil.
When patties are about half done, remove from broiler.
Combine rest of ingredients and place potato mixture on top of patties; broil until done.
Total cooking time:
about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Melt oleo in 13 x 9-inch pan and coat well.
Pour bread in pan and level off.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lo-cal "sour" cream
directions: Place all in blender; cover and blend on medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Good!

title: cinnamon loaves
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients and set aside (1/4 is for topping). Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, vanilla, sour cream and milk. Beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 batter in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon mix.
Pour rest of batter on top.
With spatula, cut through batter and swirl.
Sprinkle reserved cinnamon mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing; then cool.

title: tacozania
directions: Mix together the tomatoes and enchilada sauce or salsa; set aside. Brown the ground beef and add the taco seasoning. You can either add onions here or wait to layer them when assembling.

title: macaroni salad
directions: With macaroni, chopped celery, onion and parsley in a large bowl, combine all other ingredients except lettuce.
Stir to blend; pour over macaroni mixture.
Toss to blend; refrigerate. Serve on shredded lettuce.

title: chicken cheddar bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour and bouillon.
Gradually stir in milk and continue stirring as it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Arrange broccoli in 2-quart casserole; spoon mix over broccoli evenly.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat in a large saucepan; drain.
Stir in water, tomatoes, carrots, mushrooms, barley, garlic and oregano.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until barley is tender.
Season to taste.
Stir in Velveeta until melted. Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: frozen brown sugar cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in a couple of teaspoons of water.
Cream together sugars and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla, then add the rest of the ingredients gradually. Divide into 5 rolls 8-inches long and wrap in wax paper.
Freeze. Slice off 1/4-inch thick. Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cat fish stew
directions: Fry fat back and remove from grease, cut up onions and saute in grease until clear, add soup and catsup, salat and pepper and simmer about 1 hour, stirring often as it sticks easily. Continue cooking till fish are fork tender.
Serve over rice.
Very good when camping or on a cold day.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Cook rice with milk and cream for about 1 1/2 hours in a 2-quart double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add beaten egg, vanilla and sugar.
Stir well.
Serve warm or cool.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Heat sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed to a boil.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Drain cabbage; stir in celery, peppers, carrots and onion.
Stir vinegar mixture into cabbage mixture.
Spoon into 3 (1 pint) freezer containers.
Remove from freezer 8 hours before serving.
Place in refrigerator to thaw.

title: spoon bread
directions: Add boiling water slowly to corn meal, stirring constantly. Let stand until cool.
Mix salt, sugar and baking powder with beaten egg yolks.
Add milk.
Add milk mixture to cooled corn meal.
Beat vigorously.
Add melted shortening.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in well-greased deep baking dish or pan at 400° for about 40 minutes.
Serve by spoonfuls from baking dish.
Eat warm with butter.

title: green bean salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar and oil until sugar dissolves. Mix all other ingredients and add vinegar, sugar and oil mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Drain 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: jam cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add jam, coconut, raisins, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into floured and greased cake pans.
Will probably have to use at least 3 cake pans.
Can use four.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes before turning out of pans.
Cool completely.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Microwave Directions:
Pierce potatoes with a fork.
Microwave on High for 10 to 30 minutes or until tender, turning once halfway through cooking.
Let stand while preparing topping.
Place ground beef in a 1-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover with microwave-safe waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes or until no longer pink, stirring once and breaking into small pieces halfway through cooking time; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and corn; cover.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until very hot, stirring once halfway through cooking.
To serve, cut potatoes in half lengthwise; top with meat mixture and cheese. Yield:
6 servings (260 calories).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4
ingredients until moistened.
Form into small balls.
Melt the chocolate chips with paraffin.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Chill on waxed paper.
Use toothpicks to dip.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until tender; mash well.
Add vanilla.
Add enough sugar to make stiff dough.
Roll out on powdered sugar board and spread with peanut butter.
Roll into log and slice.

title: swedish ost kaka (egg custard)
directions: Beat eggs and add cottage cheese.
Add sugar and stir well. Add whipping cream and stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and then bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well and pour in 2 graham cracker crusts.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk and shortening to a boil.
Take off heat. Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Spoon out on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: garden cheese soup
directions: In kettle, cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add water, bouillon, pepper and vegetables; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts. Do not boil.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake and put in greased and floured 9 x 13 inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
After cake is cooled,
poke holes through with a fork.

title: rumaki
directions: Marinate water chestnuts in soy sauce for at least 1 hour. Drain chestnuts.
Roll each in brown sugar and wrap each chestnut in 1/3 strip of bacon.
Secure with a wooden toothpick.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: quick fudge frosting
directions: Mix in pan, sugar and cocoa.
Add butter, milk, syrup and salt.
Stir and bring to a full boil.
Boil vigorously, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes.
Cocoa syrup must become thick and coat the spoon.
(So be sure the mixture boils hard.)
Cool.
Beat in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add 1 cup nuts.
It is usually ready to spread after it is mixed well.
If not, let stand a few minutes, then spread.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add oil and eggs. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scrapping bowl often. Stir in carrots, nuts and raisins. Bake in floured and greased pan, 9 x 13 inch,
in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: grammy's best apple pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add water and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.

title: deep dish fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in deep pan.
Combine next six ingredients well and pour over butter.
Place fruit into batter.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Delicious made with peaches, blueberries or apples.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spread pineapple in casserole dish. Mix sugar, flour and cheese: pour over pineapple. Cover with crushed crackers. Pour melted butter on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crackers are brown. If adding nuts, roast them before mixing them with crushed crackers.

title: chocolate oaties
directions: Cream together the sugar and margarine; add next 6 ingredients, blending well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Place by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan butter, milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in marshmallows, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir 1 minute.
Pour in 8-inch pan.

title: no knead cinnamon rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast on lukewarm water in large bowl.
Add sugar, egg, oil and salt.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour; mix well with hands.
Remove dough from bowl.
Grease bowl and return dough.
Cover with towel; let rise in warm place until double in bulk, approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down.
Divide into 2 balls.
Roll or pull out to rectangle 12 to 18 inches.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter or oleo.
Spread enough to cover dough. Sprinkle brown sugar, 3/4 cup to cover and 1/4 cup cinnamon.
Roll up and pinch ends.
Place cut side down on greased 8-inch cake pan. Let rise again until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Cool and frost.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: skinny shake(low calorie-like shake and bake)
directions: Put bread crumbs in deep bowl; stir in oil with a fork until evenly distributed.
Add seasonings and stir.
Can be stored in refrigerator or until ready to bake chicken.

title: banana split cake (no bake)
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and melted oleo; press into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish (casserole).
Beat sugar, butter, egg yolks and vanilla until creamy.
Spread over crust.
Layer on pineapple and bananas.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Top with cherries and pecans; chill at least 4 hours.

title: ice box rolls
directions: Place shortening and butter in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add eggs, sugar, salt, and cold water to first mixture.
Add yeast. Stir in 4 c. flour til smooth.
Then add 4 more c. flour and mix well.
Place in a greased bowl, let stand in refrigerator covered at least 4 hours or overnight.
Punch down.
Place on floured surface and knead lightly.
Shape into rolls, place in greased pan, let rise till double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Yield - 4 dozen.

title: joyce's cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften and combine with cheese and ranch dressing mix.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: louise's baked apples
directions: Cream sugar, butter, flour and vanilla together.
Add the water.
Pare apples and quarter them.
Place in baking dish and pour mixture over all.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake until apples are tender at 350°

title: always moist pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 6 eggs, one at a time, and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Add cake flour, alternating with whipping cream.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
It is the whipping cream that makes the pound cake so moist.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Bone and skin chicken breasts.
Arrange in lightly greased casserole dish.
Top each breast with cheese.
Combine soup and wine.
Mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herbed fish and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine hot bouillon, uncooked rice and seasonings.
Top with sliced carrots. Bake covered at 375° for 15 minutes.
Add fish fillets and sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake covered at 375° for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Stir rice.
Top fish with Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: english toffee
directions: Cut chocolate fine; melt in double boiler over lukewarm water (115°; higher heat causes chocolate to grey and streak).
Stir occasionally.
Slice 1 cup almonds in halves lengthwise.
Coarse chop remainder of nuts.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Place Tater Tots on top of meat.
Pour undiluted soup on top of Tater Tots. Spread cheese on top of all this and bake until hot throughout.
Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl on low speed, combine cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and 2 teaspoons pumpkin spice until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of 15 x 10-inch pan.

title: ray's favorite italian beef
directions: Fry onion, celery and pepper in margarine and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients with cooked vegetable and bake in a large baking dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda, eggs and fruit cocktail.
Mix well, pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, coconut and powdered sugar before baking.
Bake 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna and corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan and cook onion until soft. Stir in curry powder, paprika and flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly over moderate heat.
Gradually add stock and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk, lemon peel and corn, simmering 5 minutes.
Break tuna into flakes and stir into soup. Add Parmesan cheese and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve.
Yum!!

title: new england banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add all-bran and egg, then beat well.
Add water, bananas and maple flavoring. Thoroughly mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Stir in raisins and nuts, if desired.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased pan.
Cook in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: potato soup deluxe
directions: Cook potatoes (after you have cut into small pieces and cooked chopped onions with them), also chopped celery and bacon bits. When potatoes are done, put in butter.
Pour in milk to top of pan and take biscuits and drop small round balls into potato soup boiling.
When all biscuits are in, cover and simmer until dumplings are done in soup.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Knead it well.
Let it sit in the refrigerator until cold.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add syrup, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix.
Pour in an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: butterscotch no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pudding.
Add to oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: old fashion stack cake
directions: Sift flour into large bowl, adding dry ingredients in order given. Mix quickly and thoroughly into soft dough. Bake in thin layers of any size you want.

title: one pot chops(lazy man's delight)
directions: Season chops to taste allowing 30 minutes to set.

title: meat balls
directions: Add all ingredients except 2 cups juice and sugar. Shape into balls and pour remaining juice over balls and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cut fettuccine until al dente.
Return to pan.
Over low heat gently toss with cream, cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Heat until butter melts and mixture is heated through.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 main dishes.

title: boeuf bourguignon(beef stew in wine; french)
directions: In skillet, render bacon until browned.
Remove bacon and add beef (cut in cubes) in small batches.
Brown on all sides (if necessary, add butter and simmer).
Add carrots, onions, garlic, bay leaf, thyme, wine and salt and pepper.
Simmer for 2 hours. Saute mushrooms until lightly browned.
Add mushrooms to stew and cook for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Dish may be made up to 2 days ahead and refrigerated.
Serve with noodles and wine.
Serves 6.

title: low carb jello-key lime pie
directions: Boil sugar-free Key Lime Pop and add to the dry Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Add 1 cup sour cream and whip until the sour cream is blended.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: shrimp cocktail drink
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender; add other ingredients.
Season to taste with garlic powder, celery salt, seasoned salt, etc.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put salad in fridge until cool.

title: thanksgiving relish(excellent)
directions: Wash berries and apples; core, but do not peel apples.
Peel all but one orange.
Put all of this through grinder.
Add can of crushed pineapple and 2 cups sugar; stir and blend well.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine all liquid ingredients.
Float strawberries on top. Serves 15.

title: crock-pot turkey with mushroom gravy
directions: Rub salt and pepper over breast.
Make cuts 2-inches apart through meat.
Place in crock-pot.
Melt cubes in hot water and mix with soup and mushrooms.
Pour over turkey and cook on high 3 to 4 hours.
Lower heat and cook 4 to 5 more hours. Turn halfway through cooking time.

title: greek scallops(low-fat recipe)
directions: In a 9-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add onion, garlic and basil; cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and dill.
Reduce to low and add scallops.
Cook until they turn opaque.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Slice eggplant and sprinkle it with salt.
Leave it 15 minutes, then wash it and dry it with paper towel.
Heat oil and fry eggplant and bell peppers until golden brown.
Drain it on paper towel.
Fry garlic in 2 tablespoons oil until lightly golden.
Add vinegar and tomato until boil.
Arrange eggplant and peppers in a saucepan.
Pour the tomato mixture over it.
Let it cook for 10 minutes, until the sauce thickens.
Let it cool, then serve.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.
May use muffin tins.
Bake a little less time.

title: cajun turkey vegetable loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray or grease lightly.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Place in prepared baking dish and shape into 9 x 6-inch loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until juices run clear.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: chili cheese roll
directions: Soften cheese; blend mayonnaise, salt, nuts, garlic and red pepper with fork.
Make into 2 logs about 8-inches long.
Sprinkle chili powder and paprika on wax paper and roll log in it to cover. Wrap logs in wax paper and chill for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: vegetable lo mein
directions: *Mirin is a sweet rice vinegar.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Lightly butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
In heavy 5 quart saucepan, combine sugar, salt, cocoa, milk and corn syrup. Cook, stirring over medium heat, until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, to 234° on candy thermometer or until a little in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat. Add butter.
Do not stir.
Let cool until pan feels lukewarm.
Add vanilla with wooden spoon; beat fudge until creamy, no longer glossy.
Stir nuts in quickly.
Turn evenly into prepared pan. Refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan (greased light).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mini loaves for 20 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon of water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in oil in a frypan. Drain fat.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, onion and seasonings. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Just before serving, sprinkle with cheeses and heat until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with additional oregano leaves or parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans. Mash the sweet potatoes and syrup in a large mixing bowl. Add the cake mix, eggs, oil and cinnamon. Blend with an electric mixer for 1 minute on low speed. Scrape down sides of bowl. Increase the mixer speed to medium and beat 2 or 3
minutes more. Scrape bowl sides again. Batter should be well combined and thickened. Divide into the 2 pans and bake 28 to 31 minutes. Place on wire racks to cool.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together, then add whipped topping
and
whip.
Pour into baked pie crust and put cherry pie filling on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the tang and dry pudding in a bowl.
Add pineapple and it's juice and stir.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine
the
first
4 ingredients in a greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake (uncovered) in a slow oven at about 275° to 300° for about 2 hours. Stir occasionally
during first
hour
of
baking.
Add
raisins
and finish baking, stirring in brown crust as it forms on top.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil to a soft boil stage (240°).
This takes about 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove and add 4 tablespoons butter, 8 to 10 drops red food color and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Beat by hand until firm.
Drop onto buttered wax paper.
Use a jar ring to make round.

title: italian pasta bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in mostaccioli, spaghetti sauce, and 1/2 cup parmesan cheese.
Spoon into 9x13 inch baking dish. Top with mozzarella cheese and remaining 1/4 cup parmesan cheese. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: pound cake sauce
directions: Cook until thick.
Add 1/2 pint whipped cream.
Pour over cake and serve.

title: steak calzone
directions: Roll dough into a 12-inch circle.
Fry steak with onion and drain.
On half of circle of dough, put Ricotta cheese with a dash of black pepper.
Covering
Ricotta cheese, put steak, mushrooms and Provolone (put in this order).
Fold over other half of dough to make half moon, covering and sealing firmly.
Sprinkle flour on top; let bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°, until golden.

title: peanut butter and jelly popcorn balls
directions: Put popped popcorn into large bowl.
Melt peanut butter and jelly in 2 separate pots on stove.
Pour melted peanut butter and jelly on popcorn; stir (let cool for 5 minutes before touching). Grease hands with butter.
Shape popcorn mixture into small balls; place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: ravishing russian dip
directions: Mix together.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Fill hollowed out pumpernickel bread and use as a dipper.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vinegar.
Slice onions; add beets.
Pour oil mixture over beets.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine half of peaches and 1/4 cup milk in blender.
Process until smooth.
Transfer to a medium bowl and repeat with remaining peaches.
Set aside.
Combine 2 1/2 cups milk and next 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat 8 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in peach mixture and peach nectar.
Pour into 4-quart electric freezer and proceed to make as directed.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread on hamburger buns on both sides.
Put 1 slice each of ham and cheese.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mixture makes enough spread for approximately 10 buns.

title: foiled-cooked chuck steak
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place foil in baking dish; place meat on foil.
Stir together mushroom soup and dry onion mix.
Spread on meat.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle with water.
Fold foil and seal.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.

title: potatoes puffs(leftover mashed potatoes)
directions: Combine above ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoons into hot fat. They puff up very nicely.

title: sauted fresh maine haddock
directions: Marinate haddock in lemon juice, salt and pepper (4 to 6 hours). Dip haddock in beaten egg, then coat haddock in flour by shaking in a plastic bag. Fry in vegetable oil in large nonstick skillet. Turn and brown fish on both sides until flaky. Add additional lemon juice if desired.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and saute hamburger, green pepper, onion, salt, pepper, garlic salt and paprika.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Add sour cream and soup.
Stir well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter and cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at
a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Then add flavorings. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Mix with cream cheese.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Place one teaspoon of filling in mushroom. Place in baking dish and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Any extra filling can be sprinkled on top of mushrooms.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Chill.
Top with lemon drops.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 3-quart casserole dish with nonstick vegetable coating.
Cook rice according to package directions, omitting any butter or margarine called for (this takes about 5 minutes).
While rice is cooking, combine cream cheese and soup, mix until smooth and creamy.
Add Cheddar cheese, onion and thawed broccoli and mix well.
Add cooked rice and again mix well.
Spoon mixture in prepared casserole and bake until it is golden brown, about 50 minutes.

title: apple pies
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add eggs and margarine; stir.
Then stir in apples.
Place into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown. Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: layered salad
directions: In large bowl, layer in first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Evenly spread mayonnaise on top.
Cover.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss just before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat well.
Pour into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top. Bake in 325° oven until firm.

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Add dry ingredients.
Add water and vanilla. Mix until flour is dampened.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Pour into paper lined 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in slow 325° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove.
When completely cool, sift confectioners sugar on top.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add all the ingredients and mix slightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco, sugars, honey, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed of mixer until well blended. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture. Stir in oats, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Drop onto baking sheet and bake 7 to 8 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Broil until lightly browned.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add taco mix and water; simmer 5 minutes.
Spread crescent rolls in ungreased pie pans up on sides and make an edge.
Spread half of crushed Doritos over crust.
Add beef mixture, then sour cream.
Add cheese and top with remainder of Doritos.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until crust is brown. When ready to serve, add lettuce, tomatoes and bottled taco sauce to taste.

title: shelby's orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Add frozen orange juice and stir until dissolved.
Let cool in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Stir in oranges and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill dough.
Shape into "fingers".
Bake on cookie sheet in slow oven (325°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell when cooled.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix together and serve.
Celery seed or seasoned pepper may be added, if desired.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into dry ingredients only until batter is moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch or one 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: one minute fudge frosting
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla and beat until of spreading consistency.
Spread on cake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage wedges until tender.
Combine soup and cream cheese.
Top cabbage that has been placed in casserole dish. Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gran connie's fruit crisp
directions: Mix together.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam.
Cover bottom with fruit of choice (blueberries, apples, peaches, strawberries). Spread mixture on top, then cut 1 stick of butter into pats and place all over top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Brown sausage; drain. Add the remaining ingredients and put in a crock-pot until cheese is melted.

title: fruit cocktail baked dessert
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together.
Add well beaten egg, fruit cocktail (drained), 2 1/2 tablespoons of liquid from fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Stir lightly.
Pour into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Over top, spread crumbled 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
May be served with whipped cream, ice cream or lemon sauce.

title: lime pickles
directions: Mix the lime, water and cucumbers in container.
Can use a plastic bucket with good results.
Let stand 24 hours.
Then, wash at least 5 times in cold water and cover with fresh water.
Let stand for 3 hours and drain.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add cucumbers and let stand for another 24 hours.
Heat for 35 minutes; place in jars and seal.

title: fruited caramel squares
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add drained fruit and nuts. Turn mixture into well greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine melted butter and sugar and pour over top of batter.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Form ground beef into mini-meatballs.
Brown mini-meatballs in skillet and drain.
Mix Heinz chili sauce and currant jelly together.
Heat in medium saucepan until melted (preferably on low heat).
Combine meatballs and sauce and simmer.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in a shallow casserole dish.
Sprinkle over mixture the brown sugar, cocoa and hot water. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix salt, sugar and shortening together.
Then add 2 cups hot water.
Mix with flour.
Let rise to twice its bulk.
Knead and cut into rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: surprise salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil. Remove from heat.

title: irish coffee
directions: Pour the first 5 ingredients into a blender and blend.
Pour into a small saucepan and heat on medium just before boiling. Pour into a mug and top with the whipped cream.

title: low cholesterol new york-style cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray sides of a 9-inch springform pan with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.

title: raw apple cookies
directions: Sift flour, brown sugar, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix shortening, egg and milk or juice.
Add 1/2 of flour mixture with the raisins, nuts and apples.
Place on greased cookie sheet by heaping teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 45 to 50 cookies.

title: caramels
directions: Butter or Pam spray a jelly roll pan. Coarsely chop nuts onto pan.
Cook sugar, Karo and milk in heavy pan to 240° on candy thermometer. Stir constantly. Add butter. Cook to 245°.
Add vanilla and pour onto prepared pan. Scrape pan into small dish to prevent candy from becoming sugary. Cool without moving pan. Score and cut. Wrap pieces.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients except crushed potato chips.
Put potato chips on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chuckwagon baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble.
Fry ground beef and onion in bacon grease until brown.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad(congealed)
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juices.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add reserved juices with enough water to measure 1 3/4 cups and mix well.
Add blueberries and pineapple to liquid mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate until firm. Combine remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Blend until smooth and spread over gelatin mixture.
Sprinkle pecans on top and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Let pineapple and sugar come to a boil, then add gelatin dissolved in water.
Remove from heat.
When mixture begins to set and cool, add cream cheese, smoothed out and whipped, whipped cream and cherries.
Let cool and set in refrigerator.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven pan; drain bacon. Use drippings and fry chopped onions, green pepper, olives, bacon, salt, garlic powder and pepper, then add 3 cans of tomato sauce or paste, then enough water to bring to a boil.
Then add rice, stir and cover rice and cook rice as usual.

title: chocolate delights
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add cream cheese and vanilla; mix well. Cool to room temperature.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: favorite cheese ball
directions: Grate or grind cheeses; add other ingredients except for 1/4 cup parsley.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining parsley. Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook and mash potatoes.
Add butter, milk, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add eggs last.
Mix and pour into greased baking dish and bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.
(If runny in the middle, cook a little longer.)
If desired, put marshmallows on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger with green pepper and onion and salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.	Add tomato sauce, kidney beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in buttered dish.
Cover each breast with cheese slice.
Combine soup, water and juice.
Pour over chicken; season to taste.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken.
Spray with vegetable spray or drizzle 3 tablespoons butter over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Overbaking makes chicken tough and dry.

title: nanny's yum yum cake
directions: Combine all items except flour.
Bring to boil and boil 10 minutes; cool completely.
Add flour and baking soda.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix and cook apples with other ingredients until thickened. Pack apples in jars and pour liquid over and seal.
Process 20 minutes in hot water bath.

title: apricot bread pudding(with lemon butter sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Melt butter in 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Combine bread with the milk/syrup mixture. Mix and set aside. In another bowl, combine eggs, sugar, and lemon juice. Mix well and then add to bread mixture along with the chopped apricots. Stir until well mixed. Pour into pan. Bake for 1 hour. Serve with Lemon Butter Sauce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together using 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise to begin with.
Add another if needed.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: In large bowl, combine water and concentrates.
Add cranberry juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Before serving, very slowly add pink Catawba juice.
Stir gently.
Makes 24 (4 ounce) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar.
Sprinkle 1/2 over bottom pie crust.
Pour in pudding after it is made according to directions on box.
Top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle the remaining peanut mixture over top.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: veal ala swiss
directions: Cook cutlet, top with tomatoes (breaded and browned).
Add avocado and Swiss cheese.
Put lid on top until cheese melts. Serve with potato or rice.

title: filipino chicken
directions: Place all the ingredients in a skillet, cover and cook on top of stove over low heat for about 45 minutes.

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes; cut into wedges.
Let stand in cold water for 1 hour or more.
Rinse and dry well.
In heavy roaster, put small amount of oil and heat over burner.
Add potato wedges; sprinkle with seasonings as desired.
Toss lightly.
Cut 1 stick oleo into small pats and place over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 1/2 hours.
When lightly browned, turn with spatula and continue baking.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make tablespoon size cookies on ungreased tins.
Bake at 365° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: lelia ann's cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese in mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese, garlic cheese, smoke cheese (if using) and margarine.
Cover.
Leave out overnight.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in dry place.
Use a heaping 1 1/2 teaspoons per cup.
Pour on boiling water.
(This is a very soothing beverage for colds and sore throats!)

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: This casserole is prepared almost as you would mashed potatoes.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13 cake pan. While still hot, punch holes in cake with fork. Pour the sweetened condensed milk over cake. Place Butterfinger (crumbled) over cake next. Let cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: hersey bar pie
directions: Place Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler; heat until candy and marshmallows are melted.
Cool in refrigerator until mixture begins
to congeal.
Whip the cream, and fold until the candy-marshmallow mixture is thoroughly combined.
Pour into pie shell and chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: rich and chewy pralines
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup together until candy thermometer reaches 245°.
Remove from heat and add butter. Stir until dissolved.
Add whipping cream slowly. Return to heat and cook until candy thermometer again reaches 245°, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop on foil that has been buttered. When cool, wrap in plastic wrap. Makes about 40.

title: kisses
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff (with electric mixer).
Add light brown sugar and beat until satin looking.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Spoon dabs onto pan with a teaspoon.
Press pecan halves in the center of dabs.
Preheat oven to 225°.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Let set in oven 20 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into a dry measuring cup and level with knife.
Combine first 5 ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir in milk and vanilla extract.
Spoon batter into 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine brown sugar and 3 tablespoons cocoa. Sprinkle over cake batter.
Pour hot water over batter but do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched in center.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Melt 2 sticks of margarine; pour into bowl and mix well.
Place mixture in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan and flatten with the back of a spoon.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine and the chocolate chips over low heat. Spread on top of mixture in pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into small squares or bars.

title: split-pea soup
directions: In Dutch oven or large kettle over medium heat, heat ham bone, split peas, carrots, onion and 7 cups water to boiling.

title: melissa's cocktail dip
directions: Rinse some of the salt
off the beef.
Mix all ingredients and heat for 25 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, cheese, onion, celery and mayonnaise. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: Stew and skin chicken and dice.
Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Saute onion and pepper in margarine.
Salt to taste.
Mix mushroom soup and chicken broth with flour.
Mix all together and pour in large casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: tropical pudding
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and bring to a boil.
Combine sugar and flour; add water to make a smooth paste.
Add to pineapple juice and bring to boil.
Add beaten eggs and cook 1 minute.
Cool thoroughly, then add pineapple, 3 bananas and marshmallows.
Mixed nuts may also be added, if desired.

title: soap paint
directions: Combine chicken, beef, pork, water, salt, corn syrup, spices, autolyzed yeast, natural flavorings, sodium nitrate and dried garlic (can be found at Bi-Lo labeled Vienna Sausage).
Place wiener on soda cracker and place entire cracker in mouth.
Wash down with Co-coler.
Serves 4.

title: oil pastry
directions: Mix up and roll out between two sheets of wax paper.
Makes 2 crusts.

title: snow peas with cashews
directions: Wash pea pods; trim ends and remove strings.
Cook in a small amount of boiling water for 5 minutes, then drain.
Cook frozen peas in a small amount of water for 3 minutes, then drain. Combine peas in a large bowl and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add cashews, green onions and garlic, cooking for 1 minute.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour over peas and toss gently.

title: peanut butter punch(weight gain)
directions: Blend all on high speed. Serve as food supplement for high energy and weight gain.

title: simple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter or margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, then at 350° for 30 minutes more or until it test done.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes in pan.

title: soy sauce chicken or pork chops
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish, skin side down.
Add water, soy sauce and cut up onion.
After 45 minutes, turn chicken over.
Baste often.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: wheat germ molasses muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Blend wet ingredients.
Stir wet with dry just until blended.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 350° for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully and test with a toothpick for doneness.

title: nancy's coffee cake(very easy to prepare)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: chocolate chunk pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla extract in medium bowl with a wire whisk. Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle chunks over bottom of crust.
Pour pecan mixture into pie shell.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from center comes out with little bits of filling attached.
If browning to quickly, cover with foil.
Cook for 2 hours.
Refrigerate until served.

title: summer salad
directions: Pour over veggies, coating well. Cover and chill well.

title: easy red beans and rice
directions: Cook sausage over low heat 5 to 8 minutes. Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Drain, if necessary. Add beans, tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Serve over rice. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage pie
directions: Scramble sausage; drain well.
In a bowl, mix eggs, milk and cheese.
Add the salt and pepper to taste.
Add the sausage and mix.
Pour into the pie shell and bake at 350° until done, usually about 30 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until boiling.
Boil about 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Pour over corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Bake crust in strips or rounds, except for top (save this). Use granite pan.

title: chili
directions: Preheat a 6-quart roaster oven to 425° (I use a Nesco roaster oven).
Lightly spray cookwell with spray cooking oil.
Break apart the meat; place in preheated cookwell.
Add onion and garlic.
Cover; cook 10 to 12 minutes or until meat is browned, stirring once.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed. Reduce temperature to 325°.
Cover.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes or until flavors blend.

title: le jean's butter tarts
directions: Mix butter with flour as for pie crust.
Dissolve yeast in sour cream and add beaten egg yolks.
Add to flour mixture and beat with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll out 1/3 at a time on a board sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Cut out rounds with cookie cutter.
Put 1 teaspoon of any desired pie filling in center of each; fold over to make little turnovers or leave flat.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: sausage and vegetable casserole
directions: Spray a large casserole dish with Pam.
Layer potatoes, onion, carrots and pepper.
Pour tomatoes and water over ingredients in a dish.
Place sausage on top and add salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brunch casserole(overnight)
directions: Brown link sausages. Cut up in small pieces. Drain on paper towel.
Beat eggs in a large bowl. Stir in mushroom soup and evaporated milk. Cube the bread. Add bread and cheese to the rest of the ingredients.
Put in casserole or flat baking pan.
Keep in refrigerator overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Great for a morning get together or brunch.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan; bring to rolling boil.
