Stir constantly.
Keep boiling 5 minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Pour in a greased pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: pork and apple supper
directions: Place apples in a well greased casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and spices together. Sprinkle over apples.
Coat chops with Shake 'N Bake and arrange over apples.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 375° to 400° oven for about 1 hour.

title: peach delight
directions: Drain and chop	peaches,
save peach juice.
Add 2 cups boiling water to Jell-O;
stir well.
Then add 1 1/2 cups cold water and
the
peach
juice.
Put	in
refrigerator.
When it starts to jell,
take
out	and stir.
Add chopped peaches and put back
in refrigerator.
Take paper towels and blot cottage cheese; get as much
moisture
out	as
possible.
Then add to Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Then beat in Cool Whip. When ready to serve, beat again.

title: refrigerator dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and brown sugar.
Spread 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise.
Place in a 9 x 13 inch pan with filling side up.
Spread can of well drained pineapple on top of Twinkies.
Mix pudding according directions on box.
Spread on top of pineapple.
Slice bananas and layer on top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over entire cake.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake in three layers.
Boil sugar, Pet milk, margarine and vanilla until thick (approximately 10 minutes).
Mix in coconut and chocolate frosting.
Spread coconut mix between each layer and on side.
Spread remaining frosting over entire cake.

title: super-healthy chicken soup(under 300 calories; serves 4)
directions: Place chicken parts, water, celery, salt, pepper and tomatoes in pressure cooker.
(Do not fill cooker more than 2/3 full.) Cover and follow owner's manual carefully.
Cook at 15 pounds pressure for 20 minutes.
Reduce pressure and remove chicken from pot; skim off fat.
Add onion soup mix and cabbage; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
While ingredients are simmering, remove chicken from bones, discarding skin and bones.
Chop chicken into bite size pieces; return to pressure cooker.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Contains 242 calories per serving.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add milk and remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: italian country bread
directions: Next:
Add yeast to sponge, water, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat with a whisk 3 minutes.
Add remaining flour until pulls away from sides.
Turn onto floured surface and knead about 5 minutes.
Slam the dough hard against work surface.
Set aside, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Knead again.

title: "whities"
directions: Blend oleo, brown sugar and white sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Add other ingredients (except chips).
Spread in a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Place in 350° oven for 2 or 3 minutes to melt chips.
Marbleize chips and return to oven for about 15 minutes.

title: southern fried corn
directions: Shuck corn; wash and remove silk.
After cutting the kernels in half with a sharp knife, cut kernels off.
Scrape juice out of corn cob into the corn.
Heat drippings in large, heavy skillet. Add corn, flour, sugar, water, milk and salt and pepper to taste. Bring mixture to boil, stirring constantly.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer until corn is tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: In large bowl mix sugar, egg, margarine and molasses.
Measure 1 cup of flour and mix this into sugar/molasses mixture.
Add baking soda, cloves, cinnamon, ginger and salt, then add remaining 4 cups flour alternately with the milk.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes after dropping from spoon.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: In 2-quart glass measure or bowl, combine all ingredients. Heat, covered, with wax paper, at Medium 11 to 13 minutes or until pudding is thickened, stir three times.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cinnamon crisp(very good)
directions: Mix.
Cook until starts bubbling.
Add nuts.
Spread on cinnamon crackers broken into individuals that have been placed on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 7 minutes.

title: yummy healthy muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine bran, cereal, oats and boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add melted butter, eggs, buttermilk, molasses, honey, vanilla and raisins.
In a large bowl, blend flours, soda and salt.
Add liquid to dry ingredients; mix lightly just until blended.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes one dozen regular or 6 large muffins.

title: jeannine's pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough according to package directions; divide in half.
Roll out very thin.
Brush with egg and oregano. Spread pepperoni on dough, then Provolone cheese on top of pepperoni.
Brush again with egg mixture.
Roll up and place on slightly oiled cookie sheet.
Brush top with rest of egg mixture; may need to use another egg if this is not enough.
Repeat same directions on second piece of bread.
Both loaves fit on same pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm as appetizer, or may be served like pizza with a salad for a light dinner.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Brown meat on both sides in 8-quart pot.
Add all ingredients except flour and water.
Simmer 3 1/2 hours until tender; remove meat and mix the flour and water.
Add to pot and thicken with mixture.
Return meat to pot.
Serve over pasta, mashed potatoes or cooked rice.

title: fondant-dipped strawberries
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, combine sugar, lemon juice and corn syrup.
Cook, stirring until mixture is smooth and thin enough to coat berries.
Remove from heat; keep fondant warm over hot water.
Holding berries by the stem, dip each into fondant, covering halfway.
Place berries on wire rack to dry. Makes 12.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Make traditional mashed potatoes (enough to fill 13 x 9-inch glass pan).
Mix in 2 envelopes Lipton cream of chicken Cup-a-Soup.
Sprinkle in 2 tablespoons chives.
Spread 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° approximately 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Clean and wash seeds; dry.
Saute seeds in butter and salt. Stir 3 minutes.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: blt chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, barbecue sauce, onion, lemon juice and pepper in a bowl and mix well.
Cover and chill.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes and chicken; toss to mix.
Just before serving, place salad on individual salad plates.
Spoon dressing over salad and sprinkle with bacon.
Garnish with egg slices.

title: easy homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put stew beef and onion soup mix in large stew pot (6 to 8 quarts) with 2 quarts water.
Cook at least 1 1/2 hours, then add tomato sauce and a can of water.
Cook 30 minutes or longer.
Then add Veg-All and can of water.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Pot should be covered while cooking.
At this point, uncover and boil a little harder and add pasta.
Cook about 7 or 8 minutes and move off burner.
Soup tastes better if made a day ahead.

title: cheese ball (blue cheese)
directions: Mix well.
Add onion salt, garlic salt, Worcestershire and Lawry's salt.
Roll in pecans.

title: crustless ham and asparagus quiche
directions: Place asparagus in bottom of a 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and onion over.
Combine eggs with milk and salt. Pour over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and set in refrigerator overnight.
Stir occasionally.
Be sure to cover.

title: eastern shore macaroni salad
directions: Combine cooked macaroni to all other ingredients. Flake tuna and also add the oil.
Add spices to taste.
Chill and garnish with paprika.

title: pork tenderloin and herbs
directions: Combine bread crumbs with herbs.
Cut eight slits in meat to hold onion wedges.
Brush meat with mustard and roll in herbs and bread crumbs.
Roast in oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until juices run clear.
Remove pork from pan.
Place pan on medium heat; add apple cider.
Boil until thickened; add 2 teaspoons Dijon mustard and salt.
Strain sauce and serve on the side.
Cut pork into 1-inch thick slices.
Serves 4.

title: peach cream cheesecake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Combine first 7 ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into pie plate.
Pour over batter the sliced peaches.
Combine and beat the cream cheese, sugar and reserved juices for 2 minutes.
Spoon over peaches to within one inch of sides.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion, garlic, bell pepper and celery until soft.
Blend in flour and add all remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes, depending on size.
Do not overcook shrimp.
Serve hot over rice.

title: sugar 'n spice carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy and slightly thick.
Add carrots and oil; blend well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: bride's bowl punch
directions: Chill all ingredients except
club
soda
for
2 hours. Add thinly sliced strawberries for garnish.
Add 2 quarts soda just before serving.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve first 4 ingredients together.
Dissolve next 3 ingredients together.
Beat the eggs.
Then put all liquids together and pour over flour; mix together.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll round and spread top with soft butter, then cut each into 16 wedges.
Roll in horn by starting to roll at large end.
Place on greased baking sheet with point on underside.
Let rise for four to six hours.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with butter.
Makes 32 rolls.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Empty can of crushed pineapple in a saucepan.
Add 2 cups water.
Bring to boil.
Stir in large package of orange Jell-O. Let set.
When cool, stir in 1 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Let set until fairly firm, then fold in 1 carton of Cool Whip.
Yummy!

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook celery and onion in oil over low heat until tender in large pot.
Then add tomatoes (mashed in blender), paste, sauce, sugar, chili powder, Worcestershire, Tabasco, salt and garlic salt.
To this, add shrimp and bell pepper and simmer 45 minutes. When ready to serve, dissolve the cornstarch in water and add to thicken.
Serve over rice.
Makes about six servings.

title: tuna rarebit
directions: Dilute cream of mushroom soup with milk.
Put in double boiler and stir in Velveeta cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Have water boiling and stir until cheese melts.
Add tuna.
Serve on bread, toast or crackers.

title: grandma's raisin pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water and raisins.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and butter.
Pour into a pastry lined pie pan (filling will be thin).
Cover with top crust; seal the fluted edges.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375°.
Bake 30 more minutes or until crust is golden.

title: hot buttered rum cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.
Return cake to pan.
Prick surface of cake at 1-inch intervals with a wooden pick; pour 1 cup Butter Sauce over cake.
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on a serving plate.
Garnish, if desired.
Pour remaining 1/3 cup Butter Sauce over cake and strawberries, if desired.
Yield:
One 10-inch cake.

title: rhode island johnnycakes
directions: Put corn meal and salt into medium size mixing bowl.
Bring water to boil.
Let boiling water dribble onto corn meal while stirring constantly, then stir milk into mixture; it will be fairly thick, not runny.
Heat griddle or heavy skillet and grease generously with bacon drippings.
Drop the batter by spoonfuls onto griddle.
Flatten them with spoon or spatula to 1/4-inch. Fry until brown, then turn and brown on other side.
Serve with maple syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan large enough to hold mushrooms.
Use low heat.
Add soy sauce.
Add washed (and halved if large) mushrooms.
Let simmer on lowest heat for at least 1/2 hour.
Serve warm.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil.
Add peppers, carrots and garlic; cook and stir.
Mix soy sauce, pineapple and juice, vinegar, sugar, ginger, ketchup and cornstarch.
Bring to a full boil. Pour over chicken.
Mix well.

title: quiche
directions: Place Swiss cheese in pie shell.
Top with ham, cheese or bacon.
Mix half and half, Cheddar, eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over pie.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pear halves, reserving syrup.
Add cold water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add syrup-water mixture.
Chill until thickened, about 1 1/2 hours.
Dice pears and set aside.
Fold 1/2 cup thickened Jell-O into whipped topping.
If necessary, chill again until mixture will mold. Carefully line serving bowl with the Jell-O and whipped topping mixture, molding high at edges to form a shell.
Add pears to remaining Jell-O mixture, carefully spooning into center of Jell-O mold.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk and rice in large saucepan over low heat for 1 hour or until thickened; stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
In a separate bowl, mix well eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Pour into serving dish and sprinkle with cinnamon; chill until firm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix flour, cheese, salt and pepper in bag.
Moisten potatoes. Put flour mixture in a bag with potatoes.
Shake potatoes in bag to coat with the mixture.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring to a boil milk, peanut butter, sugar and corn syrup. Cook to a soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and rolled oats.
Mix. Drop onto wax paper by the spoonful.

title: my favorite popcorn
directions: Air pop popcorn, spray with Pam spray and sprinkle with spice mixture (equal amounts
of	cinnamon,
Equal
and Butter Buds). Place top on bowl and
shake.
Eat until your heart is content.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spread all in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper until almost tender in oleo.
Set aside.
If using pork sausage, brown and drain off fat.
Using a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, spray with a cooking spray, then put bread pieces on bottom of baking pan.
Layer the meat mixture, then the cheese.
In blender or mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cheese will rise to top.
Serves 8.

title: chunky cream cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon extract; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: lime pie
directions: Add sweetened condensed milk, lemon flavoring and food coloring to lime juice concentrate.
Stir well, then fold in Cool Whip (reserve a little dollop on top of finished pie).
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Garnish with remaining Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Line bottom and sides of baking dish with tortillas.
Mix other ingredients (except the 2 cheeses) together. Mix 1/2 mixture on top of tortillas.
Arrange another layer of tortillas.
Then add rest of mixture.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with cheese; place back in oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: hidden valley ranch holiday torta
directions: Cream the cream cheese and salad dressing mix together.
In a separate bowl, stir together artichokes, peppers and parsley.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Cook hamburger with onion and garlic, then drain grease.
Cook all the rest of ingredients until desired doneness.
Water can be added if necessary but only use a little, if needed.

title: spinach lasagne(serves 8)
directions: Combine eggs, Ricotta cheese, spinach, garlic, basil and Monterey Jack cheese, mixing well.
Arrange half noodles in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Carefully spread 1/2 spinach mix over noodles.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over this.
(May use Parmesan also.)
Repeat layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: scotcheroo cookies
directions: Heat sugar and Karo but do not boil.
Add peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir well; press lightly into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt over hot water in a double boiler the chocolate chips and butterscotch bits.
Spread over mixture evenly.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in big bowl.
Drain pineapple and mix with eggs, oil, vanilla, nuts and mashed bananas in medium bowl. Add the moist mixture to dry mixture.
Spray the Bundt pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 70 to 75 minutes.

title: burgoo
directions: Cook together the first 8 ingredients with enough water until done. Simmer all ingredients until thick.

title: raspberry cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Butter and flour two cake pans (round ones work best, 9 x 9 pans work, too). Put in fridge until ready to use. Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Set aside. In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with mixer until very light.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add the flour mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Add vanilla.

Pour into baking pans. Bake until cakes are light golden, about 30-35 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes and invert onto cooling rack to cool completely. Place one of the cakes on a serving plate and spread the jam over it. Warm the jam first to make it easier to spread over the cake bottom.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Slowly cook syrup, salt and sugar until it boils.
Gradually pour hot syrup over beaten eggs.
Cool.
Add pecans and vanilla flavoring.
Pour in 8-inch pie shell.
Cook 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce oven to 350° and cook 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add sherbet and ice cream.
Stir until ice cream is partially dissolved.
Add ginger ale and stir very slightly as not to lose fizz.
Serves 25.
(Can be cut in 1/2 for a smaller group.)

title: wimpies
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let cook on low for a few minutes. Flavor is richer if cooked longer. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: chicken in chablis
directions: Bone and skin chicken breasts and sprinkle with salt and nutmeg on both sides.
Brown in butter.
Add onion, mushrooms and 2/3 cup of Chablis.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove chicken to warm platter.
Bring pan juices to a boil and cook, stirring until liquid is slightly reduced.
Stir in a mixture of cornstarch and 2 teaspoons Chablis.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Spoon sauce over chicken.

title: peanut pie
directions: Blend
cream cheese, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and milk until smooth.	Fold in Cool Whip; pour into crust and top pie with peanuts.
Freeze.
Do not thaw before cutting and serving pie.
Must be made ahead.
Keep frozen.

title: oriental toss
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Combine remaining ingredients in covered container, shaking to mix well. Pour over salad, tossing to mix well.

title: canned green beans
directions: Just cover beans with water boil for 45 minutes after they start boiling, turning with wooden spoon along while boiling. Pack beans in hot jars.
Cover with liquid from beans and seal.

title: giant cookie
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla together in a separate bowl.
Mix the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and baking powder together and add to the cream mixture.
Add the chocolate chips, grated chocolate and chopped nuts.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet or round throw away pizza tin.
Place in oven set at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Decorate and serve.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all together and bake.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut roast into bite size pieces and marinate in wine or salad oil for at least 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients and wrap in foil paper in baking dish and bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Set caps aside and chop up stems finely.
Saute stems and onions in oil.
In bowl, mix other ingredients.
Add sauteed ingredients and just enough water to moisten., Fill the mushroom caps and place in buttered pan or sprayed with Pam.
Put a small piece of butter on each mushroom and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: forget-me cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually, then beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Fold in vanilla, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven at least 8 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and simmer caps a few minutes. Brown sausage; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender, drain and mash slightly. Mix cornbread mix as directed and stir in nacho soup and chilies. Add squash to mixture and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; top with Cheddar cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: hot tamales
directions: In blender, combine onion, water and tomatoes.
Puree.
Then combine all other ingredients and mix.
Roll small amount lightly in corn meal and wrap lightly in paper.
Place tamales in large pot.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Toss with chicken and celery.
Cover and refrigerate.
When cool, stir in grapes.

title: vonie's rhubarb nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and
oil.
Beat in egg. Add flour, soda and salt alternately with
milk
until
blended.
Stir in rhubarb, vanilla and nuts.
Turn
into
2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Sprinkle top with
sugar
and
cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: zesty eggs
directions: Place all ingredients except butter into a bowl and beat with a fork until blended.
Melt butter in a 1-quart glass casserole in microwave oven (about 30 seconds on High).
Pour eggs mixture into casserole.
Cook uncovered 3 to 4 minutes on High or until almost set.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Remove from oven; stir and let stand covered a few minutes before serving.
Serves 2.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix all together in large mixing bowl. Bake in greased pans 1 1/4 to 2 hours for loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Cook onion and pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir often. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: exotic, yet simple spanikopita(greek spinach pie)
directions: Mix spinach, onion pieces, dill and Feta in bowl; add eggs and lemon juice.
Layer fillo brushed with butter to 8 to 10 layers and bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased glass pan at 350° until light brown. Spread spinach mixture over fillo.
Repeat layering on top of spinach.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and fillo is browned (medium).
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Measure flour and salt into a large bowl or into the work bowl of a food processor with the steel blade in place.
Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in lard until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Or, cut in using food processor.
With processor on, or stirring with a fork, add enough tepid water to make a stiff, smooth dough.

title: stir-fry chicken bowl
directions: Cut chicken cutlets into strips.
Set aside.
Clean and cut scallions into 1-inch lengths.
Set aside.
Cut broccoli spears into 1/4-inch diagonal slices . Set aside.
In large skillet or wok, pour 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
Saute chicken, scallions and garlic about 2 minutes or until chicken turns white.
Add water chestnuts and broccoli and stir-fry 5 minutes until crisp-tender. In small bowl, pour 1/4 cup soy sauce plus 5 dashes Tabasco into 1 cup chicken broth.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Stir well. Stir cornstarch mixture into skillet mixture.
Bring to a boil and simmer until sauce thickens (about 5 minutes).
Serve with cooked rice or chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: corn pudding
directions: *May substitute vanilla extract and reduce milk by 1 cup and add 1/2 teaspoon baking powder to make pudding thicker.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and chocolate in a small saucepan over low heat.
Combine sugar, eggs, flour, milk and vanilla, stirring well.
Gradually add chocolate mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into pastry shell; bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables(sugar-free)
directions: Drain peas, corn, green beans and pimento. Dice celery, onion and carrots. Mix together all of the ingredients, adding Equal, salt, pepper, vinegar and oil. Stir well.
Put in refrigerator. Will keep several days.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with the envelope of dry soup.
Spread the pretzels on cookie sheet.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over pretzels. Bake in oven at about 200° to 250° for 15 minutes, then pour remaining mixture over pretzels and bake again for 15 minutes.

title: cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour glass baking dish. In the bottom of dish, spread pecans and cover with coconut.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour batter over pecans and coconut in dish.
Blend together cream cheese and butter in a separate bowl. Slowly add sugar until all is blended smoothly.
Spread cheese mixture over prepared cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in slowly sugar; add eggs, unbeaten, one at a time.
Put nutmeg and raisins through food chopper and add the flour, sifted with salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add to the mixture with the milk.
Stir orange rind and flavorings.
Pour into a large 10-inch pound cake pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken biscuits
directions: Cook the chicken and pick off the bones.
Heat together the soup, water or chicken broth and cheese until cheese melts.
Pour half of the cheese mixture in casserole dish, then roll out canned biscuits and fill with chicken.
Fold biscuit over and seal with a fork.
Lay chicken biscuits in casserole dish on the cheese mixture.
Pour the rest of the cheese mixture over the biscuits. Bake at 375° until biscuits are baked.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese and dry dressing.
Spread on rye bread. Slice cucumber and place slice on each half.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Chill in refrigerator until serving time.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Put Sugar in double boiler.
Butter Bread and stack and cut into pieces.
Place in double boiler on top of Sugar.
Sprinkle Raisins over Bread.
Slightly beat Eggs.
Add Vanilla, Salt and Milk.
Pour over Bread cubes (do not stir).
Place over simmering water and cook for 1-1/2 hours.

title: party potatoes
directions: Put thawed potatoes on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except corn flakes, and pour over potatoes. Crumble corn flakes or crackers over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Place all tomatoes in a large cooking pot.
Cut up onion and garlic; simmer in olive oil until they just begin to smell (be careful not to overcook these!).
Place garlic and onion in cooking pot.
Add next 10 ingredients (wine through salt and pepper) to cooking pot.
With so many tomatoes, there will be an acid taste, so add just enough sugar to balance it out.
Bring sauce to a quick boil for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Lower the temperature; simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: honey butter
directions: Let butter stand at room temperature until softened. Gradually add honey until well blended with butter.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries (halve the larger ones) in baked and cooled pie shell.
Cook together Jell-O, cornstarch, sugar and water until it comes to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over strawberries; chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken balls
directions: Beat cheese and mayonnaise until blended.
Add rest of the ingredients, except coconut.
Mix well.
Chill about 1 hour. Shape into chicken balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Makes 30 or so small chicken balls.

title: diabetic banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender. Alternate layers of drained carrots, pepper and onion slices (thinly cut).
Make marinade of remaining ingredients, beating until well blended.
Heat marinade until hot, almost a boil, then pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: beef and leeks in spicy chili sauce
directions: Heat wok or 12-inch skillet over high heat.
Add oil; rotate wok to coat side.
Add beef and leeks; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add broccoli mixture; stir-fry about 4 minutes or until beef is brown and vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in chili puree; cook and stir about 30 seconds or until hot.
Serve with rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across the grain into very thin strips.
In skillet over high heat, cook meat and onion until meat is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through; keep stirring.
Reduce heat to very low; stir in sour cream. Gently heat through.
Serve over noodles.
Recipe may be doubled. Serves 6.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and chocolate.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip and shaved chocolate. Makes 1 pie.

title: green chile casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rice, green chiles, celery soup and sour cream together.
Grate Velveeta cheese on top of mixture.
Mix this together and add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: sherry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 5 minutes in large bowl.
Pour in greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Prepare pie crust mix for a 9-inch pastry shell with a high, fluted edge.
Chill.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl until foamy.
Add 2 tablespoons of the sugar slowly, beating until meringue forms soft peaks.
Beat egg yolks and the remaining sugar in a medium sized bowl until thick and light. Beat in flour, lemon rind, lemon juice, milk and butter until smooth.
Fold into meringue until no streaks of white remain. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Do not overbake.

title: girl scout cookies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Stir in peppermint oil.
Dip crackers in chocolate and put on cookie sheets covered with waxed paper. Refrigerate until chocolate is solid.
Then remove to a container and store in refrigerator.

title: virginia apple nut pie cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased pie pan. Dot with 2 tablespoons oleo. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: untossed salad
directions: Cover bottom of deep, clear-glass bowl with fresh, raw spinach.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and sugar over spinach.
Add bacon to spinach, then eggs.
Cover with lettuce, salt, pepper and sugar.
Spread peas over the lettuce and cover them with slices of red sweet onions.
Add mayonnaise over top like icing.
Cover with strips of Swiss cheese.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: deluxe waffles
directions: Place dry ingredients in bowl.
Combine buttermilk and eggs and add to flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in melted butter.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large mixing bowl, beat butter with electric mixer. Set mixer at medium speed until butter is fluffy. Add sugars. Beat well. Add egg, egg whites and vanilla; blend well. Add banana; beat on high for 30 seconds. In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder. Add flour mixture alternately with cream to butter mixture. End with flour mixture. Add walnuts. Grease and flour loaf pan. Pour in batter. Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Top of bread should split. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack for 10 minutes. Remove bread from pan and cool completely before slicing. Store wrapped in plastic wrap.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add eggs and oil, mixing completely with electric mixer.
Fold in bananas, nuts and pineapple.
Bake in a large tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry.
Cook sugar, syrup and water until soft ball stage is formed.

Pour 1/2 syrup over beaten egg whites and beat while remaining syrup cooks to hard ball or brittle stage. Remove this last cooking from low heat, add first syrup and egg mixture to kettle and beat until it will almost hold, or slightly stiff.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Beat with wooden spoon until it will not move.
Beginning at edge of pan, remove by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Do not add nuts while syrup is too hot as it draws oil from nuts and will not hold up.
Also, do not overcook.

title: fried potatoes
directions: You will need heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Take a medium size casserole or pan and lay a large piece of foil in bottom.
Bring up sides to fold over top of potatoes.
Cube potatoes and put in foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with oleo; sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Close foil over potatoes, sealing tightly. Bake at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sheila's chicken ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together in food processor.
Form into ball and chill.
Roll in chopped pecans. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour in a buttered casserole in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Bake cornbread; cool and crumble in large bowl.
Chop onions and celery; cover with water and boil until tender (using chicken bouillon cubes in water).
Mix the following with cornbread:
egg, pepper, butter, salt, poultry seasoning, sage and chicken broth (adding 1 can of broth at a time).
Add onion and celery mix to cornbread mixture.
Bake at 400° in 2 pans.

title: dump peach cobbler cake
directions: Beat flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk together.
Put into casserole dish.
Melt margarine and pour into middle of mixture.
Do not mix.
Pour can of peaches on top of margarine. Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Will brown and crisp as crust rises to the top.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine milk, pudding mix and whipped topping in bowl; mix well.
Stir into creamed mixture.

title: stir-fried pineapple chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin slices.
Heat several tablespoons of oil in bottom of wok.
Add pineapple, several dashes of salt and enough broth to cover.
Cook for 11 minutes.
Add chicken and cornstarch, diluted in water to make a thick paste, sesame oil, brandy, soy sauce and sugar.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Chop stems.
Saute onions in butter.
Add stems and bread crumbs.
Stir over heat.
Add parsley.
Season (pepper, salt or garlic salt).
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff mushrooms.
Bake in buttered dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sarma(stuffed cabbage rolls)
directions: Remove the core from a head of cabbage.
Put the head in a large pot of boiling water to which 1 tablespoon salt was added. Cook 5 minutes, until leaves soften a bit.
Meanwhile, fry garlic and onion in oil until soft.
Add meat and fry until brown.
Turn off heat and add seasonings and rice.
Let cool and add eggs.
Mix well.

title: janice jackson's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Keep refrigerated.

title: irish setter
directions: Fill blender with ice; pour liquor over ice.
Add 2 ounces half and half or whipping cream; fill to the top of blender with Coke.

title: green beans au gratin
directions: If using fresh green beans, wash, string and break into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook, covered, until tender (about 25 minutes). Drain and set aside.

title: english peas and new potatoes
directions: Cook frozen English peas according to directions; drain.
Cook peeled white potatoes until tender; drain.
Mix English peas and new potatoes.
Cover with half and half cream.

title: sandra's chicken enchiladas
directions: In small frying pan, place oil.
Heat, dip
and remove tortillas to soften, one at a time.
Place 2 tablespoons cheese, 1 1/2 tablespoons chicken and 2 tablespoons onion on each tortilla shell.
Roll up and place, seam side down.
In saucepan, melt butter and flour; blend well. Slowly add broth and cook, stirring until thickened.
Stir in sour cream and green chilies.
Heat through.
Pour over prepared tortillas in baking pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake 5 minutes more.
(This recipe can easily be doubled.)

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Blend in flour.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes without browning.
Add scalded milk, seasonings and cauliflower.
Cook until smooth and slightly thick, stirring frequently. Just before serving, add shredded cheese and stir until melted.

title: ham and cheese potato bake with cheese
directions: Butter 4-quart casserole dish.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter over medium heat until soft, but not brown (5 minutes). Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Simmer, stirring until thickened (2 minutes).
Stir in 1 cup cheese and mustard.
Cook, stirring until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Gently fold in potatoes, carrots and ham.
Pour into prepared casserole dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: two cabbage stir-fry
directions: Combine vinegar, water, soy sauce and cornstarch in a small dish; mix well and set aside.
Heat oil in a wok or heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and ginger root; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add red and green cabbage.
Stir-fry for 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Add vinegar mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 servings.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 of onions. Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions. Bake for 5 additional minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Add enough water to mixture to moisten it, but not too watery.
Must hold together enough to drop into hot grease.
Brown on one side and turn to brown on the other.
Makes 15 to 20 hush puppies.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and noodles. Stir.
Layer in baking dish, beginning with sauce on bottom.
Use noodles right from box (do not cook first).
Cover and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
(I have to cut cooking time in my oven.)
Remove cover and bake for 10 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes on counter, then serve.

title: mrs. creason's jam cake
directions: Cream butter
and
gradually add sugar.
Cream together until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs.
Sift the flour before measuring and add it to spices and salt.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Steam potatoes
in
two
inches
of water until tender. Drain. Add remaining ingredients and mash until smooth.
Form into patties
1/4-inch
thick.
Place
on sprayed cookie sheet and bake at
400° for 40 minutes, turning once.
Pancakes are done when browned.
Yields 9 pancakes.

title: banana bars
directions: Combine butter and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add buttermilk and bananas; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 9 1/2 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marshmallow crispies
directions: Grease large saucepan with cooking oil.
Add marshmallows and melt over low heat.
Watch carefully.
Quickly stir in cereal.
Mix well.
With buttered spoon press into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cut into 25 squares.
Yields 25 squares.
Serving Size:
1 square. Exchange:
1 fruit.
Calories:

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugars and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 20 to 24 bars.

title: bacon wraps
directions: Mix soy sauce with ginger and sugar.
Soak water chestnuts in mix 10 minutes.
Wrap water chestnuts with bacon and broil until bacon is cooked.
Serve hot.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except clams), creaming until smooth.
Drain clams thoroughly and stir into creamed mixture. Season to taste.
Refrigerate until ready for use.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken with 3/4 cup Catalina dressing and honey in a Ziploc bag for at least an hour.
Grill chicken on barbecue or broil in oven until done, brushing with marinade often.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie shell. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix hamburger and noodles together.
Add the chopped onion and celery. Add cream of celery and cream of mushroom soup.
Put in oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chef-way deep-fry batter
directions: Blend together dry ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Make a well in center and mix in beaten egg, milk and oil.
Blend until dry ingredients are moistened.
Coat dry vegetables or etc. with batter and drop in hot 350° to 375° oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: spinach with mushrooms
directions: Cook garlic and mushrooms in butter 2 or 3 minutes or until mushrooms are partially tender.
Add spinach.
Cover.
Reduce heat when steam forms; cook 3 to 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice. Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: leg of lamb with garlic and rosemary
directions: Pat lamb dry and score fat by making shallow cuts all over with tip of a sharp small knife.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into half moons. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 275°. Cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Sift again.
Cream shortening; add sugar and gradually cream together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes, or until browned.

title: bean casserole and beef
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add all other ingredients and bake in a casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: aunt hazel's corn fritters
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to liquid to make 1 cup.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine beaten egg, milk mixture and corn; add to dry ingredients, mixing until moist. Drop by tablespoon into hot grease.
Fry until brown; drain on paper towels.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Mash and blend real well.
Mix rest of ingredients together blending well.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
This pie needs to be baked in deep dish pie shell.

title: tammy's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour
and
sugar.
Bring to a boil margarine, cocoa, and	water.	Pour
this over flour, sugar mixture and beat well.
Mix	together
eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into previous mixture and beat.
Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet
and
bake
about
minutes at 400°. Start the icing when cake is about half baked.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in ReaLemon juice and vanilla. Pour into pie shell and chill for 3 hours.
Spread cherries on top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls size of walnut (no larger).
Chill 2 hours.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Keep in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: billie's chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt together in large bowl.
Combine butter, Crisco, water and cocoa in pan and bring just to a boil. Remove from heat and pour over dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix well. Beat in eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 15 cake pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minute at 325°.
When done, and while cake is still hot, punch holes all over cake (with handle end of small wooden spoon).	Have frosting ready and spread all over cake.
Pour some in holes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Break stick of butter into 6 chunks on top of mixture.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Soften gelatin in lemon juice, then dissolve over hot water.
Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise and salt.
Stir in gelatin.
Whip cream until stiff, gradually adding sugar during last stages of beating.
Fold in cheese mixture, nuts and fruit cocktail.
Pour into refrigerator tray that has been lined with waxed paper.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Turn out on platter; remove paper and cut into thick slices.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash with mixer.
Add sugar and cinnamon. Fill bottom of dish with mixture.
Put layer of marshmallows, butter and coconut.
Then alternate layers until dish is full.
Put marshmallows on top.
Brown for a few minutes at 300° until marshmallows melt.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients and stir lightly to just moisturize dry ingredients.
Mixture will be thick and lumpy. Drop by spoonfuls, spreading batter with spoon. Have pan hot.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Very good on chicken!

title: popover apples
directions: Chop apples.
Spread evenly in a greased 10-inch pie plate. Beat eggs on high speed until foamy.
Add flour, sugar, milk, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Beat on low speed until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350 for 50-60 minutes until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve with whipped Cream or Ice Cream.

title: wild rice pilaf
directions: Rinse and drain wild rice.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice, almonds, mushrooms and green onions.
Saute for 20 minutes or until almonds are brown.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bring chicken broth to a boil in skillet.
Pour over rice mixture; mix well.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until all liquid is absorbed.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Stir fruit into sour cream. (Prepare a while before you plan to serve.) You may substitute fruit of your choice. It is easy and delicious and can be served as a salad or dessert.

title: angel food pie
directions: Mix Jell-O.
Cut angel food cake into 5 to 6 rings.
Put a layer of Cool Whip, marshmallows, cake, then Jell-O.
Continue doing layers until topped with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with candies or marshmallows as desired.

title: spanish sauce
directions: Put the Mazola in a saucepan; add the mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Fry 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, Karo and seasonings.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Thicken with the cornstarch dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add olives.

title: apple fritter rings
directions: Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Combine eggs and milk; add to dry ingredients, stirring well. Peel, core, and slice each apple into 1/4 inch-thick rings.
Dip apple slices into batter, and fry in deep, hot oil (375°).
Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes or until fritters are golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 12 to 14 slices.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Form into small balls.
Melt chocoalte chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Use two forks to dip balls in chocolate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chopped onion and defrosted broccoli. Allow to simmer while preparing rice according to directions on box.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Melt the butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and cook until mixture is thick.
Blend in seasonings and cheese and cook until the cheese melts.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into the 3 egg yolks which have been beaten.
Fold in the cooked spinach.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. May be iced with favorite icing or sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Freeze in large containers.
Remove 5 1/2 hours before serving.
Chop to a juice and add 3 (1 liter) bottles Wink.

title: pumpkin raisin drops
directions: Mix egg, pumpkin, brown sugar, oil and vanilla in bowl.
In another bowl mix rest of ingredients. Combine both mixtures and stir in 1/4 cup raisins.

title: caramel cake frosting
directions: Boil sugars and milk until syrup forms a soft ball in cold water (232°).
Add butter; remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm (110°).
Beat until thick and creamy and of right consistency to spread.
Will cover top and sides of two 9-inch layers.

title: impossible chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Grease 10 x 12-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under cold running water to thaw; drain.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups of cheese, chicken and onion in pie plate.

title: montana trail-baked beefsteak
directions: Have the steak cut thin.
Roll it in flour and place in an ordinary baking pan.
Season with pepper, salt and butter.
Pour hot water on until nearly covered.
Put in the oven, cover and cook until tender.
This is much more convenient than the ordinary way of cooking steak.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Mix milk
with
gelatin.
Place
over low heat and stir until gelatin
dissolves.
Stir
in egg yolks and brown sugar. Continue stirring
until brown sugar dissolves.
Mix pumpkin, sour
cream, cinnamon,
cloves,
nutmeg
and
salt.
Stir
in gelatin mixture. Whip egg whites, gradually adding granulated sugar,
until
stiff peaks
form.
Fold into pumpkin mixture. Pour into cooled pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or longer before cutting.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sausage crescent rolls(delicious)
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan.
Drain.
Soften cream cheese and mix with sausage.
Make crescent rolls, using sausage mixture as a filling.
Cook on cookie sheet (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Brush with butter when taken out of oven.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and moisten with mayonnaise.
Serve on rye bread.
Makes a whole lot!

title: easy beef stew
directions: Dredge meat with flour.
Heat oil in heavy skillet or Dutch oven; brown meat on all sides.
Add soup, water, sherry, salt and pepper; cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Stir frequently. If the gravy becomes too thick, add a small amount of water as necessary.
Shortly before serving, add cooked peas and carrots. Other vegetables may be used as desired.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Combine cereal, coconut, sugar, butter and nuts.
Pack 1/2 mixture into 7 x 11-inch pan.
Spread softened ice cream over mixture.
Spread remaining crumbs on top and freeze until firm.

title: cheesy bread sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine biscuit mix and milk in large mixing bowl; stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Spread dough evenly in prepared pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
To serve, cut into 3 x 3/4-inch strips.
Makes about 36 bread sticks.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon and onion together.
Then add rest of ingredients. Cook awhile to thicken.

title: classic lasagne
directions: In large heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onion in oil.

Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano; simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes. Meanwhile, cook lasagne as directed; drain.
in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread about 1 cup sauce.
Then alternate layers of lasagne, sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes; cut in squares to serve.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Use pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Place crumbs, sugar and margarine in pan; mix thoroughly.
Press evenly in pan with back of a spoon.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook oleo and marshmallows.
Add salt, sugar and vanilla. Pour over popcorn; form balls.

title: pinch bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water; set aside.
In a large bowl, pour 1 cup boiling water over Crisco, to melt the Crisco. Add sugar, salt, eggs and flour; stir.
Add dissolved yeast mixture and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: georgia punch
directions: Combine concentrates and juice in chilled punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale.
Add whole block of sherbet, which takes the place of an ice ring.
Club soda can be substituted for 1 bottle of ginger ale.

title: poor man's stir-fry
directions: Steam cook cut up pieces of chicken (may season if you wish). Cook rice according to directions on box.
Drain juice from peas and carrots.
Halfway through rice cooking, add cooked chicken and vegetables.
May add small can of pineapple (optional).
Cover until all water is absorbed.

title: k & b's famous grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Set oven at broil.
Take one slice of bread and put butter on one side of it.

Lay, butter side down, on a cookie sheet, then take both slices of cheese (unwrapped) and put them on the bread. Take the other piece of bread and put butter on one side of it. Lay that piece of bread on top of the cheese.
Butter side up and place in the oven until golden brown.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb until very tender (10 to 12 minutes).
Add sugar and bring to a boil.
Add strawberry jello and boil 2 minutes. Add crushed pineapple.
Put into jars and seal immediately.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a microwave-safe dish.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Pour out on waxed paper to cool.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water; drain and cool.
Chop eggs, onions, celery and pickles very fine.
Mix ingredients; sprinkle with paprika.

title: spiced apple slices
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and spices.
Add apples and simmer, uncovered, until apples are tender, but not broken.
Pack in clean, hot jars and seal.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown ground meat.
Add taco seasoning and set aside.
In mixing bowl (large), break up lettuce.
Add tomatoes, cheese, meat and dressing.
Toss together.
Crunch up Doritos and add just before serving, if desired.

title: peanut yummies
directions: Place syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil. Remove immediately.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and cereal. Stir.
Drop.
Place in cool breeze or refrigerator.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: company clam dip
directions: Drain clams, reserving 1 tablespoon of liquid.
Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add clams, reserved clam liquid and remaining ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts and mixture is hot.
Serve with crackers and chips.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender (approximately 45 minutes).
Pour off water; let cool.
Scrape peelings with knife; dice.
Boil eggs.
Dice onion, celery and pickles.
Mix in large bowl.
Add salt.
Mix in potatoes and eggs.
In separate dish, stir mayonnaise and mustard together.
Add to mix.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and serve with assorted fruit.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix in a big bowl.

title: lemon-nectar cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 350°.
Remove from oven and let stand in cold water about 5 minutes, then turn out on plate and glaze while still warm with 1 cup powdered sugar and juice from lemon.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and enough water to equal 1 gallon. Refrigerate.

title: baked haddock
directions: On medium heat to make a roux, melt butter, then add flour; blend well.
Add milk slowly, stirring all the time.
When mixture is hot, add cheese, Tabasco sauce, horseradish and white wine. Stir constantly until thick.
Pour over fish in baking dish.
(Cut fish into serving size pieces first.)
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add buttered bread crumbs the last 5 minutes or French's onion rings, crushed.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in Crisco.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add rest of ingredients, and stir well. Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Heat the last 6 ingredients until hot.
Slice cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle on salt and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Drain.
Add cucumbers to liquid until hot.
Pack in hot jars; seal and water bath for 5 minutes.

title: easy to make cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into mixing bowl. Add shortening, milk, eggs and flavoring to other ingredients. Beat for 2 minutes with mixer.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Blend first 8 ingredients.
Add mushrooms.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator in covered glass bowl.
Drain to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Coat cut up bananas with dry pudding; add pineapple, fruit cocktail and cherries.
Toss all together.

title: fish with corn bread stuffing
directions: Cook and stir onion and celery in butter or margarine in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in cornbread stuffing mix, parsley, salt, pepper, sage and egg.
Place fish steaks in greased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 1-inch.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 2 tablespoons of lemon juice and a bit of paprika.
Spoon stuffing around fish steaks. Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until fish flakes easily with fork, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut fish steaks into halves.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts and bake in a tube pan one hour at 325°.

title: bacon rolls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add water and bring to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in stuffing mix.
Add sausage and egg; mix well. Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Shape into 24 (2 x 3/4-inch) logs; wrap a piece of bacon around each log and secure with toothpicks. Place on a rack in a broiler pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Turn logs and bake 15 minutes more or until browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Bacon rolls may be assembled and frozen unbaked.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and flour. Roll out dough to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut with cookie cutter. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes. If you want soft cookie, use buttermilk if you want a crisp cookie use water.

title: grandma elzies brown sugar cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Then add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade bologna sandwich
directions: Get checkbook or some money.
Go to deli at favorite grocery store.
Buy bologna.
Have it sliced thick to insure full flavor. Put following ingredients on table in preparation:
mustard, mayonnaise, sliced dill pickles, lettuce, tomato and bread. Remove two slices of bread from package.
Spread mayonnaise and/or mustard on both slices.
Place pickles on one slice bread.
Take one slice bologna from package.
Remove red plastic ring.
Eat leftover bologna stuck on ring.
Throw ring away.
Put bologna on top of pickles; add tomato and lettuce.
Place last slice of bread on top.
Eat and enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Thinly slice squash into casserole dish.
Dice onion over squash.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add margarine over top of squash and onion.
Beat egg into soup.
Spread soup and egg over squash casserole.
Crumble crackers over top of soup.
Grate cheese over top of crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook hamburg and sausage in skillet until brown; drain.
Add taco seasoning and minced garlic; set aside.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the following order:
nachos, vegetables, meat mixture and cheeses.
Add another layer in the same order.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients into cream cheese, saving some beef to roll ball in.
Makes 2 balls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crumble crackers and saute in butter or oleo.
Mix other ingredients and put into casserole; spread sauteed cracker crumbs evenly over top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until set in 350° oven.

title: blueberry drop cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream the shortening, sugar, egg, milk, almond extract and lemon zest. Mix well after the addition of each ingredient. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Blend into the sugar mixture. Fold in the blueberries. Cover and chill about 4 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss all ingredients.
Serve chilled.
For best flavor, chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight to let flavors mingle.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Heat to boiling the sugar, vinegar, oil, pepper and water. Cool slightly.

title: lemonade
directions: Stir together water, juice and sugar.
Pour over ice.
Makes 5 (3/4 cup) servings.
Can be doubled or tripled.

title: india relish(very good; makes 12 pints)
directions: Wash the vegetables thoroughly.
Remove stem and blossom ends of tomatoes, seeds and white portions from peppers.
Put through food chopper with onions, using medium knife.
Turn into 10-quart kettle.
Add salt; let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and cinnamon.
Boil slowly 1 hour.
Mix turmeric, mustard and flour; stir in.
Cook 15 minutes longer; stir occasionally. Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add water and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add; beat well.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 375°.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend together the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Mix in gradually with oil mixture. Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dorothy smith's chocolate reese's cup candy
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients together.
Press onto buttered tray approximately 1-inch thick.
Cover with melted chocolate bark.
Cut this into squares as soon as you pour the melted chocolate over peanut butter and sugar mixture.

title: strawberry or peach dessert
directions: Can use peaches instead of strawberries.
Add raw honey or Sweet 'N Low over berries.

title: cinnamon suckers
directions: You will need ice cream sticks.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine flour and spices. In a different bowl, beat eggs well. Add sugar and oil alternately with flour mixture and water to the beaten eggs.
Pour batter into a large tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add flour, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar in top of double boiler and melt. Cool the mixture and add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans, salt and vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool; dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: fudgelike brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with oleo over hot water (or microwave them), cool.
Beat eggs
until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition. Blend in chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour. Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, cool then cut.

title: cool pack venison
directions: Use 1 teaspoon salt and pepper per jar.
Cut meat into small chunks about an inch square (do not rinse in water).
Pack into quart jars to the neck of the jar.
Add salt and pepper to each quart.
(Do not add water.)
Put the lids on.
Put jars into canner and fill canner with cold water to the neck of the jars.
Bring to a boil and boil for 4 hours.
Add boiling water as needed in canner to keep at neck.

title: chocolate cake filling
directions: Melt chocolate.
Beat yolks until very light and fluffy and add
sugar.
Add butter, vanilla and milk.
Cook over low flame to
full
boil,
then boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add melted chocolate and beat until it holds its shape. Spread filling on layers and sides of 6 layer cake.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Choose the size dish, can use any size.
Dip cookies in milk; shake off excess and place in dish to form a layer in bottom. Spread a layer of Cool Whip over top of cookies.
Alternate layers of cookies and Cool Whip, ending with Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top, if desired.
Refrigerate for approximately 2 hours and serve.

title: sun-maid holiday hearth loaves
directions: Cream
together butter, sugar, lemon peel and cinnamon. Beat in
eggs
until light and fluffy.
Beat in milk and lemon juice. Stir
together
dry
ingredients;
add to creamed mixture, stirring
until
moistened.
Fold in apple, raisins and nuts. Spoon
batter into 3 greased miniature loaf pans, about 3 x 6-inches.
Bake
at
for
40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted
in center comes out clean.
Makes 3 loaves or batter
may
be baked in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan; then increase baking time to about 1 hour.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate squares and butter. Add sugar, salt and milk. Stir after adding each ingredient. Cook slowly about 12 minutes, stirring constantly, until begins to thicken. Refrigerate to store.

title: frosted date balls
directions: Cream together thoroughly butter and powdered sugar.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Add flour and dash of salt.
Mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until cookies are set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: crescent roll chicken
directions: Cut chicken in bite-size pieces.
Place chicken in crescent rolls.
Roll up and place in greased casserole dish, seam side down.
In saucepan, mix soups, milk and 1/2 cup cheese until heated.
Pour over crescent rolls and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: big bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix all ingredients well together.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate cream pie(low calorie recipe)
directions: Spread 1 cup whipped topping on bottom of crust.
Combine milk and pudding mix in medium bowl.
Blend with wire whisk or electric mixer at low speed for 1 minute.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spread over whipped topping.
Spread remaining whipped topping over top.
Garnish with fresh slices of strawberries if desired.
Chill pie at least 3 hours.
Makes 8 slices per pie.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain canned corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to liquid to make 1 cup.
Mix dry ingredients and add egg, milk and corn; moisten.
Drop from tablespoon into deep fat.
Fry for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: In small bowl combine soy sauce, water and cornstarch.
Stir to dissolve cornstarch; set aside.
Heat oils in large skillet over medium heat.
Add both types of cabbage, carrots, bamboo shoots and green onions.
Cook, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender, approximately 3 minutes.
Stir soy sauce mixture and drizzle over cabbage.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove skillet from heat.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix coconut with sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, make cake mix as directed.
After cooled, split layers with a thick thread to make 4 layers.
Mix coconut, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Spread between layers and on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage and egg noodle casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet.
Add onion and green pepper. Cook over medium heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Combine soup and water.
Add meat mixture, noodles, salt and pepper and mix well. Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet milk waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and shortening.
Mix well.
Add milk alternately with flour to egg mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Makes 6 servings.
(Makes great pancakes too!)

title: easy sloppy joes
directions: Combine ground chuck and onion in a large skillet.
Cook until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Pour mixture into a colander and pat dry with a paper towel.
Wipe pan drippings from skillet with a paper towel.
Return meat mixture to skillet and add remaining ingredients except buns.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes stirring frequently.
To serve, spoon 1/2 cup mixture over bun half.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown and drain sausage meat.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and turn into a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber sandwich spread
directions: Wash and grate unpeeled cucumbers using grater with 1/2 inch holes. add vinegar and salt, stir; cover and allow to stand overnight in refrigerator. Next day press out as much liquid as possible. Blend garlic salt, cream cheese and mayonnaise, combine with cucumbers.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In frypan, brown beef and onions.
Drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce, heating until hot and bubbly.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Melt butter; add onion, celery and bell pepper and cook for a few minutes.
Blend in soup and remove from heat.
Add crawfish and rice, green onions and parsley.
Blend; season to taste and place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, heat 1 cup water to boiling.
Add blueberries; return to boiling.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Mixture will be similar to thin cake batter.
Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour in cake mixture.
Add fruit and juice.
Crust will rise above fruit and cover completely.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken 'n' dressing
directions: Mix package stuffing with melted butter.
Add water; toss lightly to blend.
Place half of mixture in buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix diced chicken, onion, onion tops, salt and mayonnaise.
Spread over bread mixture.
Place other half bread mixture on top of this.
Beat eggs slightly and add milk. Pour evenly over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking; spread with cream of mushroom soup.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 2 (8 x 8-inch) baking pans.
Spread 1/2 broccoli in each pan.
Spread 1/2 turkey over each pan of broccoli.
In separate bowl, combine soup and milk; spread this mixture over turkey.
Top with cheese.

title: hot dog stew
directions: Saute onion, vinegar, oil and allspice together.

Add tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes and add diced potatoes. Add 2 tablespoons ketchup. Add water to cover potatoes and cook until done. When potatoes are done, add a can of green beans, drained. Add sliced hot dogs. Cook until done.

title: western omelet or scramble
directions: Saute all ingredients in the oil, except eggs, until onion and pepper are tender.
You may then add the eggs and scramble, or you can make an omelet.

title: german style potato salad
directions: Cut bacon into 1 inch pieces and fry, not too brown.
Remove bacon from grease and add to bowl of first 4 ingredients.
Pour some of the grease off (use your judgement).

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Slice apples thin.
Place in pastry shell.
Mix flour, sugar and cloves together.
Add sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Pour over apples.
Spread sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat; continue to bake about 40 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Drain cherries.
Sprinkle with flour until coated.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Melt butter; mix liquid ingredients and whip.
Combine both mixtures and beat until smooth and airy.
Fold in cherries.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp dip 1
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hot sauce and Worcestershire, in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add Worcestershire and hot sauce to taste.
Chill.
This is a good dip, but is also a great sandwich.

title: tacos
directions: Heat beans in saucepan.
Heat tortillas in a large skillet for about 1 to 2 minutes on each side over medium heat.
Spoon beans on tortillas and top with cheese, tomato, lettuce, avocado, sour cream, olives and green onions, if desired.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine butter, dates, coconut and sugar.
Cook on medium heat until melted.
Let cool; stir in nuts and Rice Krispies.
Let cool enough where you can hold in your hands.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together	shortening
or	butter, brown sugar and beaten egg.
Mix
cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and salt with flour by hand; add
to
creamed
mixture.	Add applesauce with soda dissolved in it.
Also
mix
well
by
hand.
Add
raisins and nuts.
Bake in 3
or
(9-inch) cake pans, greased well and lightly floured. Bake
in
oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake starts to pull from sides of pan.

title: ruth tryon's stew
directions: Brown floured beef. Add water and seasonings (lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic clove, bay leaves, salt, pepper, paprika, sugar, bouillon cube, cloves and tomato sauce). Simmer until tender, about 2 hours. Add carrots, onions and potatoes. Cook until almost done.
Remove meat and vegetables.
Thicken gravy.
Add wine (sherry, Chablis) or any wine.
Add meat and vegetables.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, heat and add 1 package frozen peas.
Cook until peas are done.

title: old fashioned lemon pie
directions: Squeeze juice from a lemon.
Recipe uses 4 tablespoons lemon juice.
Grate lemon rind outer skin to get 1 1/2 tablespoons grated zest.
In heavy saucepan, put 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and hot water.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens. Remove from heat.
Beat 1/2 cup mixture into 3 beaten egg yolks. Add to hot mixture.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and grated rind zest.
Bring to boil.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue of 3 beaten egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites and sugar until not grainy when tested by rubbing between fingers.
Brown in hot oven.
Watch carefully so it won't burn.

title: beans el charo
directions: Fry bacon in skillet lightly; do not brown.
Stir in onion, tomato, bell pepper, jalapeno peppers and garlic; add pepper, chili powder and garlic salt.
Stir-fry until tender.
Add a dash or two of Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Turn off heat and cover lightly with cilantro.
Stir into Pinto Beans Caliente during the last hour of cooking.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Mash chickpeas (partially); chop eggs, onion and celery.
Mix all together and chill.
Serve as salad or rolled in lasagna noodles, sliced in half and edges dipped in paprika.

title: mary's cheese cookies
directions: Mix margarine and cheese.
Add flour and corn flakes.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork (dip fork into water often so dough will not stick to it).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat the eggs for 1 minute.
Add the oil and sugar; beat well. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted.
Fold in the apples, which have been chopped.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: straw and hay
