directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water about 5 minutes; drain. Meanwhile, in large saucepan, combine cream, butter, ham and peas. Heat to melt butter.
Stir in noodles.
Cook about 5 minutes until noodles are tender.
Stir in cheese and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened slightly.

title: mcgregor's salad(i came up with this recipe by cleaning out the refrigerator)
directions: Dice broccoli, cabbage and onion.
Mix together.
Mix dressing to package directions.
Add dill, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over vegetable mixture.
This is best if it's allowed to set overnight.
Before serving, quarter tomatoes, then cut quarters in half and toss into salad.
This is very simple, but always a hit...my brother Marc's favorite.

title: chinese chews
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in brown sugar.
Cool slightly. Beat in eggs and vanilla; add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add pecans or coconut.
Bake at 350° until it falls.
Cool before cutting.

title: broiled dove
directions: Clean and wash dove breasts.
Put in a pot with water, butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain doves.
Serve on a platter with saltines.

title: snack pizza
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Fry sausage; stir to break up and drain
on
paper
towel.
Add to melted cheese and mix in oregano.
Spread
on party rye bread and add sliced olives on top.
Freeze on trays and then stack in cans or bags to store. When
ready
to
use,
bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot or warm.

title: spinach and corn souffle(stouffers)
directions: Leave corn and spinach in refrigerator overnight to thaw. Boil carrots in brown sugar water.
Layer spinach and corn in a glass cake pan.
Poke carrots down on top of corn.
Pour carrot juice on top of everything.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter and stir in graham crackers.
Pat mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer in order chocolate pieces, butterscotch pieces, coconut and walnuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly all over mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 36 bars.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup and milk in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake 5 minutes more.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together; set aside. Cream shortening, sugar and brown sugar together in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Add oats, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop cookies onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will be soft when they come out of oven.

title: cream puffs
directions: In a small sauce pan over med-high heat, add shortening and salt to boiling water and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously until mixture forms a ball around the spoon, leaving the pan clean.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating very thoroughly after each addition. Continue heating until mixture is thick and shiny and breaks from the spoon.
Shape on ungreased cookie sheet, using 1 teaspoon or 1 tablespoon of pastry per puff.
Bake in very hot oven - 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer. Cool.
Make slit on one side of each puff and fill with cream filling.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together oleo and peanut butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and vanilla and stir.
Press into cookie sheet.
Cut when cool.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 3 cups. Can be eaten with crackers or chunks of bread.

title: apricot bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla; mix in flour, salt and coconut.
Stir well.
Reserve 3/4 cup dough for topping; spread the rest in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread apricot preserves over mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Crumble reserved dough over topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk 1 hour.
Add egg and beat well with wooden spoon.
Add sugar and mix together well.
Add sifted flour with remaining ingredients.

title: grandmother ray's raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together the oleo, molasses, sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and stir in creamed mixture. Stir in the oats, raisins and pecans. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Heat in a skillet with 2 tablespoons oil.
Add meatballs, a few at a time, and brown slowly, turning gently to brown evenly.
Remove meatballs when brown.

title: concerto of corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven or other heavy soup pan.
Drain diced bacon on paper towel and set aside.
Cook onion, garlic and celery in bacon drippings.
Cook potatoes in separate pan in enough water to cover until tender.
Add flour to onion mixture and cook until lightly browned.
Add undiluted chicken broth and stir until well blended.
Add potatoes and water potatoes were cooked in.
Add corn and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in heavy cream and cook 10 minutes more.
Season to taste.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Butter bread on one side.
Cover the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with buttered-side down (some slices will need to be cut in half or thirds).
Layer Cheddar cheese and ham on top; place another layer of bread (buttered-side down) and then Mozzarella or Swiss.
Mix together eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over bread, ham and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with crushed corn flakes.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cream filled chocolate cookie ice cream pie
directions: You will need a 12-inch pie dish.

title: orange frosted pecans
directions: Boil the sugar and orange juice to 240°, then add the orange rind and pecans.
Turn heat off and keep stirring until cloudy looking and all nuts are coated.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add garlic and Blue cheese until melted.
Then add half and half and parsley.
Stir over medium heat until thickens slightly.
In a large pot boil the fettucini noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles, then pour Alfredo sauce over noodles and toss.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into casserole dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Melt oleo and pour over the crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and drain the fat.
Boil the noodles, drain and add to the cooked hamburger.
Add the tomato soup, pizza sauce, mushroom soup and one can of mushrooms (optional).
Mix thoroughly.
Line cake pan with one package of pepperoni and add the soup mixture.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and the other package of pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil, leaving a 9-inch overhang. Trim fat from meat.
Place in pan, sprinkle with liquid smoke and salt.
Bring long sides of foil together.
Fold up ends, crimp to seal.
Chill 8 hours or more.

title: sausage and biscuit balls
directions: Mix sausage and spices.
Take biscuit and flatten in your hand, stretching and pulling biscuit larger.
Pinch sausage and spread generously on biscuit dough.
Roll up biscuit and sausage. Pinch off small amounts and roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in accordance with directions on biscuit can.
Can be reheated in microwave easily.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Blend sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Turn into greased 9-inch pans. (This recipe makes 2 pies.)
I just spray my pans with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This pie forms its own crust.

title: jo's roast
directions: Rinse roast and place in roasting pan.
In a separate bowl, mix cream of mushroom and onion soup mix with 1 can of water and pour over roast.
Cover with foil and place in oven on 350° for 3 or 4 hours or until tender.
I put mine in on 250° and cook all day.
Check to make sure you have plenty of gravy.
If it gets low, just add water.
The last hour of cooking you can add potatoes, carrots and celery.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Mix other ingredients with wafer crumbs.
Pack into cake pans lined with wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Freezes well.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars with 1 stick margarine and set aside.
Cream sugar and remaining margarine.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour and salt, alternately, with combined soda and buttermilk.
Add melted candy and margarine and then add nuts and vanilla.
Pour in tube pan (greased and floured).
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° or in three 8-inch pans for 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with the following icing.

title: liver spread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with fork and make into ball; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Cover with cream cheese, garlic, Tabasco and salad dressing, mixed together.
Serve on crackers.

title: amaretto freeze
directions: In a blender, mix 1 1/2 cups frozen yogurt with 1/4 cup Amaretto.
Transfer to 3 chilled wine glasses.
Repeat with remaining yogurt and Amaretto.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg and serve.

title: banana nut cake(super easy)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 10-cup Bundt pan or angel food pan.

title: sweet and sour cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, soda and Sweet 'N Low together; set aside.
Mix eggs, oil, apples and vanilla.
Mix with dry ingredients and bake until done.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla and beat until well blended.

title: pizza bake
directions: Boil spaghetti 9 minutes; drain.
Add milk and beaten egg; mix well.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch or 7 x 12-inch dish.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Place on top of spaghetti.
Spread Pizza Quick on ground beef.
Layer onion, pepper, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add sugar and oil. Beat well. Combine dry ingredients. Add to mixture and beat well. Stir in zucchini, vanilla and nuts. Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: eggs and cheese casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine milk, eggs, mustard and salt.
Beat.
Stir in cheese, bread and sausage.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Test with knife.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool cake.
Mix package of vanilla instant pudding, cream cheese and milk until smooth. Spread over cooled cake.
Spread can of pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crust with crackers and melted butter and let cool.
Then pour cool pudding in crust.
Spread pineapple.
Spread banana slices.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Put in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: izzy's sausage, rice and beans
directions: In a large frying pan, saute onion, pepper and garlic powder in olive oil.
Add other spices, blending well. Cut up sausage into thirds.
Add tomato sauce to onion/pepper mixture. Cook until bubbly. Add sausage and heat thoroughly.
Keep hot on low heat.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna.
Brown hamburger and put meat in sauce and simmer.
Drain lasagna; run cold water over while fixing.
Coat bottom of pan with sauce.
Layer lasagna, sauce, Mozzarella, grated cheese and end with Mozzarella.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients and heat on slow.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream cheese and sugar; add lemon juice.
Whip milk and mix with cream cheese mixture.
Mix lemon Jell-O and plain gelatin in 1/2 cup hot water and let cool.
Mix in with cream cheese mixture until thick.
Pour into baked pastry crust or prepared graham cracker crust.

title: easy german bean soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, combine ham, ham bone, green beans with liquid and onion.
Add just enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; simmer 1 hour.
Add navy beans; cook while you prepare potatoes.
Add potatoes and simmer 30 minutes more.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix by directions on box.
Place butter in 9-inch round glass dish.
Roast for 1 minute.
Stir in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple; add cherries in center.
Add 1/2 prepared cake mix. Microwave on Simmer for 7 minutes.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: curried chicken and apple salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together yogurt, chutney and curry powder. Stir in chicken or turkey, celery, apple and green onions. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours and up to 6 hours. Before serving, stir chicken mixture. Serve on 4 kale and/or lettuce-lined plates. Makes 4 servings.

title: honey spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and honey.
Add 2 well beaten eggs.
Sift flour twice; add soda and spices.
Gradually add milk and dry ingredients, alternately, into cream mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven in a large loaf pan.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine the tuna, celery, onion, salt and pepper and mayonnaise.
Line each side of the bun with mayonnaise and a slice of Mozzarella.
Put the sides together with the tuna mixture in the middle.
Wrap each bun in tinfoil and put in a 350° oven until the cheese melts.

title: aunt mildred's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Sprinkle dry rice in long baking pan. Add soup, onion, parsley and 1 1/3 cups water or a little more. Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover in foil.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: baked eggs and sausage
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside.
In separate bowl, beat 8 eggs.
Stir in milk, bread cubes, salt and grated Cheddar cheese. Add the drained sausage.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred and cook cabbage in salt water.
Drain.
Mix soup with cabbage.
Melt cheese with margarine in saucepan and stir until cheese melts.
Mix with cabbage and pour in casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: dill dip mix
directions: Mix together equal amounts of mayonnaise and sour cream.
Add dill to taste.
Add a dash of onion salt.
Keep refrigerated.
To be used with cut up fresh uncooked vegetables such as carrots, celery, broccoli, cukes, etc.

title: french bread
directions: Put sugar, salt and shortening in a very large bowl.
Add remaining cup of very warm water and stir until ingredients have dissolved.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour and stir until batter is smooth.

title: cream puffs
directions: A house should have a cookie jar

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix zucchini, flour, cinnamon and sugar.
Now mix both bowls together. Put in loaf pans.
Makes two pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Cut into stalks and place in baking pan.
Mix soup, tomato sauce, paste, oregano and thyme.
Mix in onion and flakes.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Bake 15 minutes in preheated 375° oven.
Cover with cheese and bake 15 more minutes.
Serve right away.
Watch out, it's hot.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick. Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken. Put chicken in casserole dish. Mix soups and wine and pour over chicken.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Place ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix until blended.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken with white wine
directions: Dredge chicken in cornstarch.
Brown coated chicken in hot oil, stir in seasonings and scallions.
Cook 2 minutes longer, add broth and wine, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer another 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: czarnina(duck blood soup)
directions: To blood drained from freshly-killed animal, add 1 tablespoon vinegar and stir thoroughly.
Place in cool place, covered.
Cook stock with duck or goose giblets (gizzard, liver, heart, wings and legs which have been cleaned), soup bones and mushrooms.
Before meat is tender, add cleaned vegetables and a piece of fatback. Cook until tender; drain stock.
Soak a piece of honey cake in the stock; crush with spoon until smooth as paste and add to soup. Cook prunes in small amount of water; remove pits and cut prunes. Add with prune water to soup.
Cut giblets into thin strips and add to soup.
Add blood mixed with vinegar to soup, stirring constantly.
Bring soup to boil.
Add sugar and salt as well as vinegar to taste.
Serve immediately.
Serve with lazanki, prepared separately.

title: chocolate bit brownies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add sifted dry ingredients to first mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate bits.
Spread on large greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let cool a minute or two; cut in squares.

title: crescent bacon bites
directions: Roll crescent roll dough until thin.
Mix other ingredients, and spread on crescent rolls.
Roll up, starting with wide side. Crescent rolls will be in rectangle shape.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm enough to slice.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Serve warm.

title: sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks until light.
Mix together orange juice and rind, sweetener, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add to egg yolks.
Beat until fluffy (about 7 to 10 minutes).
Combine flour and salt.
Gently sprinkle flour mixture over egg yolks, folding in a little at a time.

title: emerald salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water; dissolve in the boiling water. Let cool, then add fruit juice and a very little green coloring. Add sugar.
When dissolved, add the nut meats and the celery, chopped fine.
Turn into a mold wet with ice water.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Turn out and serve with mayonnaise dressing on lettuce leaf.

title: barbecue sauce no. 2
directions: Combine and brush on meat.

title: mexican cheese crackers
directions: Mix together melted butter, taco seasoning, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Put crackers in a shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour taco mixture over crackers; stir well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto wax paper to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Separate mushroom caps and stems.
Mince stems and set aside. Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a skillet and cook caps over moderate heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until they begin to color. Remove and set aside.
Add the additional 1 tablespoon of butter to skillet and saute stems, onions, garlic and pepper for 4 minutes over low heat.
Add crabmeat, sherry and brandy and heat through.
Put mixture into caps, dust with cheese and bake at 450° until hot, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Remvoe from heat; stir in peanut butter. Let cool.
Pour in a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Form into balls.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake on ungreased tray until brown.
Dip in horseradish sauce.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If not moist enough, use about 1 tablespoon hot water or more.
Knead until smooth.
After rolling out, let set a minute, then cut.
Makes about 100 if you decorate, 150 to 175 undecorated.
To color, add coloring before you knead. Place in cool, dry room.

title: broccoli or cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine the rest of ingredients in mixing bowl and pour over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: country chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook broth and rice until rice is tender.
Add vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Heat thoroughly.

title: stir-fry chinese walnut chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into uniform squares about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 2 tablespoons oil.
Add chicken and stir to coat evenly.
Saute walnuts in 1 tablespoon oil until golden.
Sprinkle with salt. Heat remaining oil.
Add chicken mixture and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add ham and walnuts and stir-fry about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining soy sauce and broth, scraping up brown bits from bottom of pan; cook for one minute longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep in an open jar without cooking.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat 2 cups sweet milk to almost boiling point.
Add gelatine mixture.
Beat until creamy the sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Add to preceding mixture.
Blend and divide mixture into 3 equal parts; set aside. Beginning with yellow jello, let set in a baking dish until firm. Spoon on 1 part sour cream.
After this sets, alternate the color jello.
End with red jello.
Makes 12 servings.

title: german chocolate cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients; blend well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
tags: pudding included German chocolate cake mix

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet, cook beef until brown.
Crumble with fork and drain off fat.
Stir in soup, water and sugar; heat through. Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: apricot salad
directions: Add Jell-O to 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add apple, pineapple, cream cheese and nuts.
Pour into mold.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion.
Pour over broccoli in pan and cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix butter and stuffing mix together and sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Serves 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil. Simmer 1 hour, then bottle.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Flake salmon.
Soak bread crumbs in juice; add milk if not enough juice.

title: pork barbecue sandwiches
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine meat and water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 3/4 to 2 1/4 hours or until meat is very tender.
Remove meat from broth, reserving 1/2 cup broth.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour 2 cups of batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt caramels and margarine with condensed milk until smooth.
Spread evenly over cake; spread remaining cake batter over caramel mixture.
Top with nuts; return to oven and bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer, until cake springs back up.
Cool and garnish as desired.

title: zanaker(meatless kibby)
directions: Rinse wheat several times.
Squeeze out moisture by cupping hands.
Mix thoroughly with onion, flour, water, salt and pepper. Roll into little balls.
Drop ball into Yogurt Sauce and cook for 20 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Let cake cool.
Make holes with end of wooden spoon about 1 to 2 inches apart and pour caramel topping in holes and on top.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped up Heath bars.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add onions and partially cook.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Mix soup with milk and pour over Tater Tots.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.

title: baked omelet
directions: Beat eggs and cottage cheese in mixer bowl.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Arrange tomatoes over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: baked scallop appetizer
directions: Rinse and drain scallops.
Place in small saucepan and add wine.
Cover and simmer for 8 minutes. Drain, reserving liquid. Cut scallops into 1/2-inch slices.

title: maine fish chowder
directions: Boil haddock and bone it.
Fry salt pork and cook onions in the fat. Cook cubed potatoes in just enough salted water to cover. When potatoes are cooked, add salt pork, fat, onions, fish and scalded milk to potatoes and water.
Salt and pepper to taste. Float crackers on chowder before serving.

title: party gouda cheese
directions: Remove red wax from cheese.
Spread out pastry and press seams together.
Coat cheese ball with mustard.
Wrap dough around prepared cheese; seal seams.
Place, seam side down, on baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with cheese knife and crackers.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shortcake (strawberry)
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk, will be stiff.
Press, with spoon, into greased 9 X 9 baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: stewed codfish
directions: Soak cod in cold water for 6 to 8 hours.
Drain.
Bring cod to boil; drain and taste.
If too salty, soak in cold water.
Taste at 15 minute intervals until excess salt is removed.
Drain and set aside.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix all, except bacon.
Put in a buttered dish.
Put strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple for 1 hour.
Put oranges and pineapple in a bowl.
Sprinkle jello over it and stir.
Add cottage cheese and carton of Cool Whip.
Stir and mix together. Refrigerate to chill.

title: scotch cookies
directions: Mix together and spread thin on a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread cooled, melted German sweet chocolate over cookies.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over one half and coconut over the other half.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Place boneless chicken breasts between 2 sheets of wax paper and pound 1/4-inch thick with mallet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat butter and oil in skillet.
Cook chicken 3 minutes on each side, turning once.
Remove chicken from skillet and place in dish.
Increase heat and saute sliced mushrooms for 3 minutes. Top chicken with mushrooms and Swiss cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: oven stew
directions: Put all ingredients in greased casserole.
Pour juice over all.
Cover tightly; don't peek.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours. Serves 4 to 6 people.
Serve over biscuits/noodles.

title: mrs. baker's dish
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Brown and drain meat.
Season meat and add soup and Ro-Tel; simmer.
Boil macaroni.
Add macaroni and meat mixture.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk and stir. Turn out on well floured surface and knead 1/2 minute.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and sit for 1 hour.
Mix in pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip the whipping cream and fold in last.
Let stand overnight.

title: baked orange chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Remove chicken from skillet.	Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually add orange juice.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Stir in salt and cinnamon. Arrange chicken in greased baking dish.
Top with orange slices. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix egg, banana, oil, milk, vanilla and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients, except chips and nuts.
Mix to moisten.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: low calorie fettuccine alfredo
directions: In blender, combine cottage cheese, milk, egg yolk and pepper. Puree until smooth.
In a small saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add puree and bring to a simmer, stirring occasionally. Stir in all but the 4 teaspoons of Parmesan cheese.
Meanwhile, cook noodles according to directions; drain.
Toss with sauce. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese.
Contains 355 calories per serving.
Serves 4.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add vanilla.
Add flour, a little at a time, until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until edges begin to brown.
Cool 2 minutes. Lift with thin spatula.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and cool.
Tear up bread slices and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine rest of ingredients, including cooled sausage, and pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for burgers
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine onion, celery, green peppers and butter.
Stir in tomato sauce, lemon juice, Worcestershire, parsley, sugar, salt and pepper sauce.
Serve over barbecued or broiled burgers, pork chops or chicken (after cooking for 5 to 10 minutes).

title: mama's stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Halve and debone breasts.
Combine ham and cheese.
Find the opening or pocket in the meat and fill with the mixed ham and cheese.
Dip each in a mixture of milk and egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes or until done. Excellent with Saffron rice and green salad.

title: rocky road treats
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat.
Add milk, marshmallows and nuts.
Drop onto wax paper and chill.

title: tangy potato salad
directions: After you cook potatoes and boil eggs, mix in all the ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on bed of lettuce with small tomatoes on side.
Sprinkle paprika over for looks. Serves 5.

title: 1, 2, 3 cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, margarine, sugar and eggs, beating in eggs one at a time. Dissolve soda in about 1/2 cup milk and beat in nutmeg or vanilla.
Mix in enough flour to make the dough rollable but not too stiff as this makes cookies too tough. Roll and cut out with a large cutter, preferably crinkles around the edges.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° until lightly browned.
If you want, put a big raisin in the center of each before baking, also dust sugar on the tops.

title: easy lemon dessert
directions: Mix condensed milk, pineapple and lemonade together and fold in
the Cool Whip.
Put crushed graham crackers in bottom of 9-inch
square pan.
Pour in Cool Whip mixture and sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: make ahead mexican salad
directions: Make the salad the day	before.
Layer	in
a deep dish the lettuce, tomatoes,	onion,	avocados,
beans, dressing and cheese. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken in a casserole dish.
Add soup and sour cream. Make stuffing mix according to the box directions and then add it to the casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
In microwave, cook for 15 minutes.

title: tuna salad mold
directions: Combine the gelatin in cold water, then add hot water.
Mix all remaining ingredients well.
Add the gelatin mixture.
Pour in mold.

title: ripe tomato relish uncooked
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes and put in colander to drain. Add other ingredients to drained tomatoes and mix well. Boil sugar and vinegar and pour over tomatoes. After jars are filled and sealed boil jars in hot water for 10 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Put one slice of apple on each piece of dough.
Fold over. Place in casserole dish.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil. Pour over apples and biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sesame street potatoes
directions: Combine hash browns, soups, cream cheese, sour cream, onion, green pepper, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add sesame seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage and mostaccioli bake
directions: Prepare mostaccioli according to package directions.
Drain. In medium skillet, brown sausage and drain.
In medium bowl, blend soup, sour cream, milk, parsley flakes, salt and hot pepper sauce. Add mostaccioli and cheeses.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with smoked sausage.
Bake in a 350° oven until hot, about 30 minutes.

title: rotini and sausage
directions: Cook sausage in frying pan until lightly browned; drain. Increase heat to medium-high.
Add cream and wine and bring to a boil.
Boil gently, stirring constantly until sauce thickens slightly, about 3 minutes.
Add hot drained pasta.
Remove from heat and add Parmesan cheese.
Toss until pasta is evenly coated.

title: bundt cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add shortening, half of buttermilk and bananas.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add eggs and remaining buttermilk and beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts and pour into Bundt pan (greased) and bake at 350° until done when tested.

title: very good frosting
directions: Mix together and let stand a bit before frosting your cake.

title: potato bisque(a hearty, delicious soup for a cold winter's day.)
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft.
Add all ingredients except milk and cornstarch.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender (30 minutes).
Combine cornstarch with milk, then add to soup and cook until hot, but not boiling, stirring frequently.

title: almost like lobster
directions: Take frozen cod fillets; cover with cold water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 10 minutes, then drain water.
Cover with cold water and the vinegar.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain water.
Dip into melted butter with lemon (add a little garlic, if desired).

title: butter icing
directions: Add butter and 1/2 of sugar.
Mix until fluffy.
Add milk, vanilla and remaining sugar.
Add more milk if needed.

title: cracklin' cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, egg, milk and butter.
Beat well.
Add cracklings.
Bake in well-oiled, rectangular pan for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: libby's brownies
directions: Mix well, then either add about 1 teaspoon instant coffee or enough brewed coffee to make mixture thick enough to spread.
If using instant coffee granules, add enough hot water to mix until ready to spread.
Makes enough for about 6 people or can double this recipe.

title: piccalilli
directions: Grinding with coarse blade, sprinkle with the 1/2 cup of salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture to boiling and simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat together milk, bananas and shortening for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 more minutes.
Combine remaining dry ingredients and add to banana mixture.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: green beans with marjoram
directions: Cook green beans in 2 cups water on medium heat.
Add bouillon cubes and marjoram.
Cook until beans are tender.
Drain and serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buttermilk and pie shell.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Bake at 350° until set and brown, about 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed.
Mix all together and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake until crusty on top, 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Cream softened cream cheese; beat in sugar and Cool Whip.
Put on cooled crust.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add thawed strawberries.
Pour on top of cheese layer.
Chill; cut into squares.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar with butter.
Beat eggs and remaining sugar; combine.
Sift baking powder, salt and nutmeg with flour; add enough more flour to make dough stiff enough to roll.
Knead lightly.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and fry in deep oil.
Roll in sugar.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in canister or jar with tight lid.
For delicious hot drinks, add 2 or more teaspoonfuls to 1 cup of hot water.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Small, firm mushrooms are best for this recipe.
Wipe clean with damp cloth.
The stems should be cut off even with the top to make an attractive hors d'oeuvre.
Mix mushrooms well with cooking salt for 2 hours, then drain well.

title: spinach quesadillas
directions: Saute
cilantro,
onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil. Season with
salt and pepper.
Add spinach and cheese and heat until cheese is melted.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat egg; stir in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened and add blueberries.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: country steak
directions: Brown meat on all sides.
Add soup and water.
Mix and simmer for at least one hour.
The secret of the flavor is the cooking time so don't cook for less than one hour.
Can be cooked ahead of time and reheated.
Serve with mashed potatoes and vegetables.

title: weight watchers cranberry scones
directions: Using a fork, in large bowl combine flour, sugar, orange peel, baking powder and baking soda.
With pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add cranberries and currants.
Stir to combine.
Add buttermilk and vanilla to flour mixture and stir to combine (mixture will be dry).
Form dough into 2 equal balls.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle clean work surface with 1 tablespoon reserved flour.
Work 1/2 dough into 6-inch circle about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut circle into 6 equal wedges.
Place wedges on nonstick baking sheet, leaving a space of about 1-inch between each.
Repeat procedure, using remaining flour and dough.
Bake until lightly browned, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove scones to wire rack to cool.
